My father came from - a little place this side of - Leyburn. It's a peace called Hunton but there was a little place outside by the name of Garrison, but I can't tell you
 much about it because - you see my grandfather died when I was very young, you see that was my - my father's father. Well I was practically - little better than a little boy when he died you see but - the only thing I know that they came from round about
 Hunton, and I think it was a place called Garrison where - his father, my grandfather was a farmer you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Your father then was on the railway?
