\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
I don't know what he did you see. I only - as far as I can tell you - there was - four brothers of them and they left the farm to come into the town, you see. And - one was a joiner. One eventually got to be - he was a guard on the railway, had an acciden
t and he - he eventually got to be station master at a place called And there I think - until that place was closed down and then I think they moved to Guisborough and there he died. He died at Guisborough. He died of a cancer when he was sixty.
