My mother came from somewhere out by Catterick way. I don't know whether it wasn't Brompton-on-Swale, somewhere there. If it wasn't there it was Brompton at Northallerton and that's all I can tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you ever hear if your mother had any jobs before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Yes, she used to work at - one place she told me she worked at - I think it was, I wouldn't swear but I - I'm really sure - when a girl up to the time she was married for - she worked for Henry Pease's - Pierremont. Just for a short while.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What did she do there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 She'd be a servant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 And that's the only one you remember her having before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Yes. And she married when she was twenty, she was only twenty when she married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did she work after she married or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How many rooms were in the house at Laws Terrace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 There was two bedrooms. A front sitting ro
om as you'd call it and a kitchen, and a small back kitchen, and a yard. And of course in those days the yards - had - they were cobblestones you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Did anyone besides your parents and brothers and sisters live in the house, any relatives or lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did your mother pay anyone to help her in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
No, I don't think so unless - unless it was after the birth of a child, but I wouldn't put that down, she never employed anyone really. Just in case of emergencies you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Do you remember if the washing was done at home or sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 The washing was all done at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Do you remember wash day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes. I've helped my mother. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What did you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well I used to help her you see to ponch you see, 
there were all ponching sticks in those days. And - of course that was when I wasn't at school do you see. But }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 she did all}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588  her own washing you see, was her and - when - her daughters grew up and that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did your mother or father mend or make the families clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well they didn't make any clothes but of course they tried to keep them - something like - wearable by repairing them we'll say. But in those days it was impossible to go and buy anything just as you wanted, even a small sum of money woul
d be used. And we had a family of ten. Well - my father never had a big wage up 'til then, sometimes - I should say once upon a time when he hadn't much more than twenty shillings, and we were practically nearly all born. See. Because you see there wasn't
 a great deal of difference - there is - there wasn't a great deal of time in between each one being born.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Were the clothes you had always new or were they sometimes secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 They were never secondhand to the best of my knowledge. In those day
s they used to - wait on like one another to be a bit older. Oh they used to pay so much same as they do now you know on the credit business, buy a new suit. But of course in those days - you must understand that to clothe a family of ten must have been t
errible, I couldn't remember what they did. But I never remember - they used to just get what clothing you could. And of course you weren't very well attired, you were just simply keep simply attired, because they couldn't do it. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Were the clothes passed down from one child to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Not as I - not to my knowledge. It could have been - but not to my knowledge. Of course if there was any - any of the other girls that they could have worn you see when they were in between, well if there was anything they probably would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Do you remember where the clothes were bought, do you know where you used to get them from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Now you've got me now. We used to get them mainly - I mean to say, in those - in those days my dear there wasn't many shops so
ld clothes. No. There wasn't the shops there are today where you can go you see and - see something in the window, but - those things were practically unknown, the things were really made for you in those days. There may have been a few clothes in the win
d
ows but nothing to what you see today. In most instances, the same as one firm - there used to be someone, I couldn't tell you where they were but you see they used - get perhaps suit or two for the boys and pay so much on these, but where this firm was, 
somewhere out of the town, but I couldn't tell you now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you have clothes at any particular time of the year, new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
No, I think it was - I think - more or less - the young women in the house used to it used to be a favourite in those da
ys, I don't know just about it now but it used to be in the - used to manage to get something new for Easter time, see what I mean. And that was mainly the women you see, of course the boys it made no difference.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How about shoes, did your father mend the shoes at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Oh he was very useful that way, he'd do quite a lot. And of course - in those days - was no such things as these hairdressers and - there's one thing my father used - I always remember that, we used to talk about it, he used to tea
ch the girls how to plait their hair, do their hair. Yes. Yes. There was now here else to go those days you know. Of course he was responsible that for all such as that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Do you remember where the shoes were bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well - do you - do I 
think that - that I knew at that time they were bought in this town. But there wasn't many shops.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Any particular time for new shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Any particular time, not that I know. We used to get the boot - get the boots and shoes you see, boots and shoes - when it was possible, when you needed them, sometimes you had to go a long time before you got the new pair you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How would you make them last?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well - it was just a matter of this - the - before you got another pair and your people had to 
make some - some form of an effort - to get one child a pair at a time you see. I don't know what you're wanting to know all these things really for, but - in those days -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 It's just finding out how people lived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 I - yes I know, times were very b
ad you know. And I often think - and I'll tell you now what I mean now, I said they don't know they're born today to what they were when we were young. Yes. See - and still we got very - we got a very - we got along very nicely. And I also remember when I
 
was - about - fifteen years of age, my mother went and she got me a coat, a topcoat, an overcoat - and of course she was paying so much on this, and I also remember her words, I've a fairly good memory. But not only that, she says, you've got that coat no
w
, but, she said, the next coat you'll have to buy yourself, I was getting to fifteen year old you see. Well that coat would last me a while you see. Then after that when you got to work you had to try and provide your few things for yourself, that was - m
y
 mother a says said that. We've done all we could for you, she said - perhaps you weren't - as well dressed as you might have been because we couldn't do it. But, she said, there's one thing - out of what we had we fed you, and now its up to you to look a
fter yourself. And we all grew up to be fairly strong. And I'm not too bad now at seventy-seven. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house, such as housework or cooking or washing up, did he do anything in that line?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
No, my father wasn't a man like that, my mother used to say about - I - I've overheard her tell the story, like talking to the neighbours down there, oh, she says, you know - my man's very good but he never does anything like that. You know what I mean?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did he ever light the fires or do any decorating do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Yes. He used to do the bulk of it, whitewashing, decorating - and he was responsible for the fires and he always used - always-find a bit of wood on the railway to bring home you 
see. See? Bring home - he used to - bring little bits of wood that useless on the railway you see and chop it for kindling at home. He was responsible for all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did he ever do any repairs to the house or improvements to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 He never d
id any repairs whatsoever apart from keeping it, you know, interior decorating for your own benefit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did he ever dress or undress you or bath you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No, I think mother did all that. Mother was responsible for all that, but 
- I mean to say that in those days there wasn't the baths, we used to have what - one of those sink baths you see. And when - and we used to get into one of these zinc baths when you got to a certain age you know, the - you - I mean to say six or seven yo
u
're big - old enough to bath yourself, you know what I mean, in one of these little baths, with your mother there somewhere near hand you see, to come and see you and if you were all right. She'd examine you you see if you were all right when you were bat
hing, you were only like children. And that's how you used to wash in those days. And of course that went on for a very long time. Of course bathrooms in those days mind you were very very scarce, you would have no bathroom then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Where would you bath, in front of the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Very often in front of the fire. Yes. To keep you - in the cold weather you see, well that was to keep you from getting cold, they couldn't afford the family to be ill you see. No. You see, there was no such thing as National - 
Insurance, there was no one to help you - they had to pay their own doctor's bill, see. And when you come to think of a family my dear - it didn't want to be - anyone ill very long with a very large doctor's bill because it just simply couldn't bear them.
 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Do you ever remember your father reading to you or telling you stories?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Do I ever remember my father reading what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Reading to you or telling you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 He did nothing else. Yes. He was a very great reader, same as I was. I was
 the same always after that, reading from a paper. You see, my father - my mother hadn't an education. She could neither read - nor write. No. No. I don't know why, she could have done but of course -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 She probably never had the chance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 But - in 
that position you see she probably hadn't in those days my father you see was sent away and he was paid for, being a farmer's son. Well then he used to read all from the papers to my mother. And you see he taught us everything. I can even go back when - i
t
 seemed very difficult for me - to tell the time, and he would spend a nation of time explaining - the hours and the minutes, you see, he did all such back of you if you want, if you know what I mean. And he would read from - the paper both to us, see, be
c
ause as children we seemed to understand better when he read it, you understand what I mean, than what you did when you read - when you read it yourself. And he always read everything out of the newspapers to my mother, and he was a very big reader of boo
ks on his own account.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Did he ever just tell you stories, apart from reading, things that he'd done as a child or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Yes, he was always telling things that happened in his life. Things of course that probably wouldn't - anything 
he could remember that occurred in his life. I always remember him telling one - I don't know whether you'd be interested like but it was very good. He was a man that was very interested before he was married in going to race meetings. So he had a - he ha
d
 a friend - a man called William Clavert - he said they once went to Doncaster race, now this was my father - and - when they got to Doncaster races they - he said they only had two pound between them, that weren't bad you know, he told this story and man
y more he told, these - you know, interest kids too, but this one interested }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 one more}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588  when you grew up. He said when they got there he said to the - he said to the - to - the man that was with him, his friend, he said well - he said what about starting a bi
t of bookmaking see. What about - and they only had two pound. And you see his pal said to him he said well what in the world can we do with two pound? Well, he said, we can risk all on the first race. So anyway to cut a short - a long story short, they s
t
ood up and my father you see was - giving the horses and - he was taking the money and the other man was the clerk. It was an understood thing - that if - that - they laid this favourite, it hadn't to win, the favourite in the race. And they took everythi
n
g possible for it and put it in that bag. And I knew some arrangements, my father knew Doncaster well. Now he said, Willie, he said, now look here. He said, if this favourites' going to win, he says, you've got to - watch me, and he sayd, if he's going to
 
win he says you've got to run for your life, there's not many people there, and he says, you run to that point he says, I'll run to this point and I'll meet you there. However the horse didn't win. And he put his jockeys on like that and - oh he said, sit
 
still, he said, the horse didn't win, and they came - he said they came off the Doncaster racecourse with a hundred pound each. That's how he would - now that's a little story he told, just a little racing story you see. But any other little stories that 
he had that would interest the children with you see. Oh he was very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 patient}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588  in telling us stories you see was my father. And he was a very good talker and a very good scholar. He was just the opposite to my mother you see, but of course - they sent him awa
y, paid for his schooling, at least his father did. And he was a very good writer and a very good reader, and there - there wasn't very much reading. There was only thing as all our family said - he'd have made his way better but he was hampered by a larg
e family and small money, now you've got it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Did he ever take you out without your mother, did you ever go out just with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did we what? Well he often used to take us out, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Where would he take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Little walks round the
 - the fields you know. And then of course as we grew up you see we had a garden, he had got - he'd got a nice garden you see and - we all used to go down to garden, I was one of his chief helpers when I was about twelve year old, ten or eleven year old a
n
d every Good Friday you see - there was no going anywhere for good Friday, when Good Friday came round my dear lady I knew that we only went to one place and that was to set potatoes, all day long. You see my father was there and we - and he used to be th
e
re and - and - he used to put them in a - and used to use a line you see, and I used to have to dig the row out, and if I pressed that line back, you see, the row wouldn't be - he said, are you shoving that line back? He was a man like that. Well that's o
n
e thing I did when I were ten year old. Until I was about thirteen I used to go down all the time, and I've even gone out - when the manure was there, we had a barrow and gather so much manure for the gardens. So that's what we did in those days. You had 
i
t to do. Of course when you do things my dear lady, that was for the benefit of your own health. Well of course you had potatoes and everything you know, and he also had a bed of beautiful flowers. He grew - anything and everything in the garden that was 
a
ny - of any value. Onions, cabbages and all such as that, well - that was part of our life to help him and he was helping us. When we got to a certain age - young children now wouldn't do it you know. Oh that's too tame for them now, but we had it to do. 
W
ell that was one thing, oh my father was a very good man. There was only one thing as far as the family knew when we got up in years about - when he died, well - in some ways it was a pity because - he'd probably have got further - well like a lot more pe
ople, but he was dragged down with his family, and - the small money. That was the end of his story, but up to the end of his time he was a very good father. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 It's nice when you've got memories like that isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That's right. I can go righ
t back, and my mother was just as good, the only difference was - of course there was one thing my dear, as we all grew up you see my mother never missed her schooling because somebody did it all for her. Any - anything she wanted doing or anything - no m
a
tter whatever it was - if she wanted a letter writing to anyone a sister of mine, she would just write to her - to her sister somewhere you see, our aunt, her sister, she would say to one, well just write - they've written to her and she would read - get 
t
hem to read it to her, well she would just write back to her and my sister used to write back although she'd written. Well that was my mother's life. Well if these are the things you want to know, I'm afraid their very very interesting because they brough
t
 us up like that, and the same - and - and as I say, I'll repeat again, when we got to a certain age, now, she said, there's only on thing, she says, we'll tell you, we couldn't give you the schooling that we would have liked to have done, we couldn't hav
e dressed you - but we got all the food for you, and now that you're getting up and able to go to work it's up to you to get out and go and get something for yourself. That was my mother's words to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did your father ever look after you when your mot
her was out, did your mother ever go out on her own anywhere and leave your father to look after you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
I wouldn't say so, no, my mother never went out because she had - she had far too much to do at home with the family. Far too much to do with the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Did you have any tasks you had to carry out regularly at home to help your mother and father, there was the gardening for a start that you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Anything else you did at home to help your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes, I went out - do a little bit of work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you, to help out?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Just - I was helping one or two people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 When you were at school did you do any jobs in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 When I was - do any jobs in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You used to help your mother with the washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Sometimes we used to help that way but - there wasn't very much she ever asked the young - children to do. She always seemed to manage on her own until - the girls got bigger and then - then the girls, the boys - but it didn't concern the boys, the
 housework.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
How long did you continue to help with the washing, did you do that after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Oh no. No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
You said the girls helped your mother generally, did your other brothers have any jobs they had to do in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What sort of jobs did your sisters do in the house to help your mother?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Yes. Well - they were able to do so much housework you see such as washing floors you see - floors used to be washed in those days you see, clean u
p the fireside and - eventually they could put a fire on you see when they were quite young and my father was out. See, anything concerning cleaning, anything like that - to the best of their ability, only being young people they used to do what they coul
d, of course mother was there to see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Did you older children help the younger ones with things they found difficult such as dressing or eating, did they look after the younger children in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Only in - with regard to - probably your schoolin
g. Your intelligence you see. If there was anything you didn't know and they could tell you - you see, but as for anything else I wouldn't say they never - they never interfered with you or - assisted you in any way when you were dressing or anything like
 that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Did the younger children have any jobs they had to do for the older ones? Did you have any particular jobs you had to do for your older brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No I don't think so.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Yes, I'm afraid that - my father was rather particular. That - he was very stringent on going to bed and sometimes - we used to have to go to bed at six o'clock. Because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How old would you be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Oh probably ten or eleven you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What was the point of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
The point of it was that - I think he'd been out at work and he wanted to sit and read. You see, he'd have you so long to play and make a noise, same as kiddies do in the house, and then - he would say, now
 - off to bed those children, and then he wanted to sit and read or read to mother, I don't know what he did after that, of course we had to go to bed. But there's one thing - he always put us to bed in reasonable time, right up to being at least ten or t
welve year old you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
No, I think we could - invariably get ourselves into bed - at a very early age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What age would you be when you started to put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 I should think about - seven year old, seven year old, eight year old.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Before that would it be your mother who put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes, she would help, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
How did you all sleep, you only had two bedrooms, how did you all fit in, what were the sleeping arrangements?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
I don't know, I just forget now, of course they were only young you see. The girls all slept together you see in two beds and - sometimes you see the boys were - we were in with our father you see. We'd have a little bed in our father's room you s
ee. We - we in bed a sleep. Well - you had to sleep somewhere. See, and - of course - with a family like that, of course you were all young you see. The girls would all sleep in one you see, probably two beds and - that'd account for so many. Then of cour
se the boys, well we slept - we slept about three in a bed you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Would your mother sleep with the girls or did your mother and father have a bed downstairs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
No, they were upstairs somehow. Upstairs - somehow, they - I couldn't just tell you n
ow what - how we slept there. I know the back bedroom - that was in this house down here at Laws Terrace. There was just the two bedrooms like but - however it was so done that the girls were all in - in one room. And I don't know whether there was a - I 
don't think that - we boys were ever in there but I - I think sometimes we were sleeping in father's room - when we were quite young. But never in the girls room you see, never in the girls room. And there was just the two bedrooms in that house. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 And you shared a bed probably with two other brothers did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Two, yes. Two or three, we used to always sleep three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You say you bathed in front of the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How often did you have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 I think about every week. If moth
er felt - a little bit tired she would probably go a fortnight without doing it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 When did you have clean clothes to put on, any particular time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 About every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 After bath night would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 After bath night, yes. Probably get a cle
an shirt on or something like that. Such as you had to put on you see, put it on, it was clean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
How did your mother manage to keep you in clean clothes because you wouldn't have a lot to go on would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well that's - that - that question appear
s to me to be un the lap of the gods what - the lap of the gods where we got them because - we were always - reasonably dressed to go out you see. Sometimes we - the clothes got a bit - you know, threadbare at times, and then of course you went on until s
u
ch time as you could get another jacket on top. As long as you get one jacket you see, usually have it for - indoors, see if you got a good jacket or a - a decent pair of shoes against a shabby pair of trousers. And I suppose in those days - mother's were
 
able to make anybody a pair of trousers, you see, out of a bit of cloth. Do you know, used to be short in our day. Well - I'm afraid - it's the truth because they couldn't do any other in those days. They had to - make do and mend. That's the only way I c
an put it. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Which room did you eat in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Were there any occasions when you ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
I wouldn't say so. Unless - unless - used to have a special occasion, but it - put it down to kitchen all the time. I mean the 
special occasion might one - one or two of my aunts might come and see you but - relatives you see, but I wouldn't bother with that. Might - just for an hour or two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Where did your mother do the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Cooking - well she -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What sort of equipment did she have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Just an ordinary open fire range, you know the open fire range - in the kitchen. I don't remember any - cooking stove - cooking - cookers in those days, you know, stoves or anything like that. Before they came out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 When was breakfast eaten, what time did you have breakfast, do you remember?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Before we went to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 About what time would that be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Left school at nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 So breakfast would be about eight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Somewhere about half past eight,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What members of the family were present for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Nearly all of you when you were school age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did your mother and father have breakfast with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
If he was in of course. If he wasn't in I mean you see he worked different hours out. Mother was always there. She was there to see you got your breakfast and get out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What would your father do for his breakfast if he was on a shift?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 For his breakfast? He used to - he used to get up and do it himself. Yes.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Do you know what he had for his breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well - there wasn't much to pick and choose I mean like that - I think - the staple diet was bread and butter. Or bread and margarine, to fill up. All - they used to use a lot of fat you see, kiddies used to eat a lot of 
fatten bread in those days you know. Fatten bread, what they call fatten bread you see. In a - in - in - put it in the frying pan you see. An awful lot of that. Yes, fried bread, well you call it fried bread. We used to call it fatten bread you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you have that for your breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Sometimes. I used to like it. It wasn't a matter of I would sooner have had that as anything else as far as I know at that time and - even today that - breakfast doesn't bother me, I only have one great liking for
 anything today and that's - buttered toast. I could make my breakfast off that now. And - marmalade on you know, marmalade was always my favourite dish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 But you just had plain fatten bread did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That's right, just the bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you have anything to drink, what did you have to drink at breakfast time?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Tea. Mainly tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Was your breakfast any different on Sundays or certain days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
It could have been. It could have been when you were going to school, all depends you see. You
 used to get hold of - I mean a bit of bacon, an egg or two in those days you see, they were cheap. One - one or two week - days a week you may have a - even share an egg you see or a bit of bacon or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you have your main meal in the middle of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes. We called that dinner. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Who used to be there then, was your father with you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Oh yes, unless he was working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
If he was at work did he take a packed lunch or have it when he came back or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 He used to take it like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What sort of a packed meal would he take?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well he - he would take what he had - they used to have what they called in those days, when they worked on the railway you see you had to go out several hours, you couldn't ge
t back to your meals. Say if you went away to a place like York or anywhere like that, you couldn't get back for your dinner, you had to take something until you were back at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 So what did he take?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Had such as there was. I mean to say - the
 breath of life again, mostly bread and butter. Probably jam or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
What sort of things did you have for your dinner in the middle of the day, when you were a schoolchild, can you remember anything you had to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well there was
n't such things as - as big dinners you know. I couldn't say that when we were going to school. There wouldn't be - what you might term - roast }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 beef}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588  and three vegetables or anything like that. No. All sorts there might be - there might be even a fried egg 
or something like that. It was just a matter of what they could get hold of, even for your - main meal - even what you might call your lunch or your dinner. However we seemed to get along very well with it and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 And with your father having the garden that would help with the vegetables?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Oh yes. We always had the new potatoes you see and such as that. And - and as well you see - such as fish and chips you know - occasionally on a night. And then there used to be cakes in those days - I knew one ca
ke that was - it was very good, it was only a matter of - of a - it was a penny. Penny for this cake and they were called Lancashire parkins, you've heard of them haven't you. Well they used to be about that you see. Four - four little kiddies could get t
h
at to go to bed with you see and a cup of - milk or a cup of tea, that would do for their supper you see. Of course they were those fairly substantial inside you see for - you've heard of these Lancashire parkins. Of course you - you don't get them now. I
'
ve searched for them now but you can't get them in this town, but - in those days that little shop at the corner - oh well, you know all about parkins then. But there's not - there's no one you see can - I think that - there's no one can make parkins same
 as the people from Lancashire. Same as the people in Yorkshire for Yorkshire puddings you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you have a pudding usually with your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Occasionally. Boiled. Steamed. In - mother used to put them in these cloths you know, pudding cloths, such as that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
How often would you have meat? What sort of meat did you have when you had it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well, probably about twice a week as near as I can remember, there used to be meat on Sunday always, oh Sunday, the - dinner on a Sunday all - e
ven for the children. And vegetables just the same of course all his vegetables, he used to store his potatoes up you see. We used to go down and gather all the potatoes and everything, he grew an enormous amount of potatoes, used to carry him half way th
rough the winter. And then of course he had such things - in the cold weather as you can go and pick now, cabbages you see and brussel sprouts and all such as that,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 So about twice a week during the week you'd have meat then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Do you know what sort of meat you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Roast beef.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 This is Sunday?;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Yes, roast beef. And sometimes would last you over Monday you see. And it was made up into - what they used to call hash. And that's how it was and - anything else during the week well - such as \{BLANK\}
 such as that. As I say there wasn't - there wasn't a great deal to pick amongst and all the people - we weren't the only people, I mean to say people with large families then they did very very well to get along as well as they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 They managed marvellously.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
See - I could never understand - the - it's with the womenfolk you see that - and they were - magic with the family. Many a time they were hard - they were hard hit you know and - beat, but always managed to pull th
rough somehow. I thought - I think myself that some days - families must have gone hungry at times a little bit, until - and then of course the old stories generally so today when - when the pay day comes, the lad comes you see, my father come home with t
h
e pay you see, well he was the only - breadwinner you see, until such times as you can do as well. And when he had a large family on small money you see - well - I wouldn't like to think I would like to tackle it, start over again and do what my father di
d.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you have a tea, you had your dinner in the middle of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What was your next meal, did you have a tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Tea. And just a little bit of - a drink of something for your supper you know, didn't get much, children, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What did you eat at teatime, just bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Bread and butter and probably jam you see, because the jam was cheap enough. Marmalade and like that. Anything you could get. Sometimes you might get - the eggs were cheap you see. You might even get a - a fri
ed egg between two of you, well it - it - it fed kiddies up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Then your supper you say you sometimes had fish and chips or parkin with a drink of milk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
That's right. Fish and chips came in now and again you see. And of course you were generally r
unning along for a - a ha'porth of chips, you could get a ha'porth of chips you see in those days. Quite a number for a ha'porth of chips. And - you often got a ha'penny and - and went to the shop and got a ha'porth of chips you see and salt and pepper. W
a
lk that would feed the kiddy, he was practically full a child to go to bed. Once you got a paper of chips and used to - have a few for your money. Of course hapennies and pennies you know. Of course the fish were - the - the fish is quite cheap you see. U
sed to get a large fish in those days for a penny. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Not like today?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Oh not today. If you go to a fish and shop and they want about three or four shillings now for what you could get for three ha'pence then. And if you were to get these - what
 they call - cod slices and - so called - potatoes you know and the fish and chips - and - and the chips - well you could get them penny or ha'penny you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Was your Sunday tea any different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Sunday tea? Well you see mother might - quite possib
le bit of cake or something. \{BLANK\}
 She used to be very fond of you know of making those little - what I used to call pattacake scones or pancakes. Anything like that. And of course - sometimes children you know did used to go out gathering berries such a
s that brambles, you might get a whole host of brambles well she used to go - she used to make pies and put in it. All she had to do was find the flour and the basin and heat it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 When your father was out, when he'd taken his packed meal, did your moth
er cook for him when he came in at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Oh yes, she used to prepare for him coming in but of course in those days - she used to say - there was once upon a time she didn't know whether my father was arriving that night or three days later. See? He 
used to stay outside and he used to get so much money what they call - lodging money off the railroad you see, and they couldn't - on these long journeys they couldn't always get back my dear. I've heard here say, although I've never known it my time, he 
u
sed to be away for three days. Well of course if he came home at night, well - he would - she would have some idea within two or three hours when he would get in. And then of course she would prepare such as she had. He'd very often sit down himself you s
ee.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Have it on his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did your mother of father bake their own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Do you remember the smell of baking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
The baking day was the beauty - when you went in from school and you saw your mother at once. She had
 a great table full - of bread and teacakes. That smelt most beautiful, a thing that - I don't see now. And it was beautiful then. I would like to go into a house and see it now but I can't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 People won't go to the trouble will they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No they won'
t. And my mother was a very good baker. In fact I think all the women in those days were useful hands. As I once said you see when - a short time since when the bakers were coming out on strike - I said - you know what our mother But they wouldn't have be
en going round picking up - try and pick ten loaves up, they would - \{BLANK\}
 get some flour and get - get busy and get some bread made. I said, you don't see it now. That was Friday as near as I can tell you. Friday was the baking day. When you went in at t
eatime you were looking forward in fact to - and your mouth would fairly water when you looked in to see these - all newly freshly baked during the afternoon before you were home from school. Probably be about ten or eleven on the table and - and about ei
ght or ten teacakes you see. Well of course that went a long way you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did your mother make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 At times. At times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did she ever bottle any fruit or vegetables from the garden or anything?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No. Not in those days, not when we were young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did she ever make pickles?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Or wine or medicines for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Was any beer brewed for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did your father or mother grow their own vegetables, yes, did your father 
have fruit as well in the garden or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What sort of fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Berries. Redcurrant - redcurrant, blackcurrant you know and gooseberries, such as that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did they ever buy any fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did they ever have any tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
There wasn't very much again in those days. There wasn't much tinned stuff in those days. At least I don't remember a lot of it, today you see today - what you can see today, you see thousands of tins everywhere you 
go but - I'm afraid - they hadn't come to that stage in life when - they tinned all this fruit see what it was. The fruit that you got was more or less in - in the raw so to speak and you had to cook it yourself. Beautiful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Better for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes. I mean to say you got all the flavour from the fruit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did they keep any livestock for the family, any hens, pigs or goats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
How many times a week did you eat meat, it was about Sunday and perhaps about twice if your mother could get it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
You don't know what sort of meat you had in the middle of the week? Once it would be cold roast beef hash?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 It would be hash.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You don't remember what you'd have as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Pretty similar - again, but as far as it woul
d go you see, hashed up with potatoes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you ever have }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 corned}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588  beef or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well I don't think there was a great deal about then. I don't remember much corned beef. I can't just remember what kind of meat it was in those days, apart from - apart from the old English roast beef, and what was left of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you ever have any tinned meat, you said not corned beef didn't you?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Very rare. Can't remember much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you ever get any extra meat such as rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
No I don't think so. Sometimes some were sold round you see - on the railway you found sometimes - found a hare that had been knocked down you see - stop and pick it up. Or birds had been killed you see. Should - you be in that vicinity where t
hey were you see they picked them up - birds and bring them home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What did your mother do with those, pluck them and cook them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes, pluck them and cook them just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What did they taste like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Lovely. I mean to say they were bir
ds - probably a pheasant. Well a pheasant's beautiful. Anything like that. And - a rabbit if a - if a rabbit or hare had been killed you see, well - they'd probably - just now and again you see, well certainly I - I - I've taken them home myself before to
d
ay, I went - quite a long way to get the hare just the same. When I was on the railway and took it home. Well of course it only happened once in a - you know once in a good time. But in those days even that counted you see when you got that, that counted 
for one meal carrying into the next day sort of thing, you know, all - you lived from one day to another. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Do you ever remember seeing your mother having less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well I - I wouldn't say I can remember 
it but I quite think - most mothers in those days used to neglect themselves a little bit more for their - sort of give to the family. They would rather give it to the family you see, but of course they didn't exactly starve themselves, you know what I me
an. If there was anything that was more or less - do without themselves, I mean they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 would}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 . Naturally that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did your father have more to eat than the rest of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
I wouldn't say he was a very big eater. No. Of course going to work you see he wan
ted more. But - like everybody else - he used to take such as there was either to work or - such as there was. Any time when they came home you see well naturally I know perfectly well that - he did very well to get bread and butter, bread and margarine. 
Men - not only my father - working on all the night and had to come to - just this bread and butter for their tea. Well of course they say it's the staff of life, they seemed to live on it, and we all seemed to live on it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You all seem to have thrived 
on it, it doesn't seem to have done you any harm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes. That's right. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Probably they have too much }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 concocted}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588  food these days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well, I don't believe in it myself. I mean to say when you've got - when you've got such as there was margarine
, the butter when you could get it, anything like that, and the fresh baked bread was worth - one loaf of that was worth ten of this your buying now, I'm quite sure of that. It was - it seemed to be more nature in it you see. It was something you could ea
t
 and enjoy. How many times have people said this stuff is as wet as can be now, this bread. Other times it's dry. And then - all of a sudden - someone starts to bake some pies. I've seen people coming in now and they're baking their own pies, I've seen me
 get hold of - part of that fruit pie that's been home made. I could tell directly I took hold of it. You could bring all the stuff in my day from the shops and I'd just single a piece out and eat it. I'd say, this is homemade. Now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Were you allowed to talk during meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes, I don't think they stopped us from talking at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to have a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Your own choice - as near as I can tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
What was your parents attitude if you left some food uneaten on the plate, if you ever did that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well I - I couldn't answer that because I don't think there was very much left. I think what - what was left would - it wouldn't - do for anything apart from the birds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
If there was something on the table that you wanted like the salt, could you ask someone to pass it to you or did you have to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You could pass it - you could ask for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Yes. You could. You weren't always allowed because your parents thought - you had enough, and what sort of thing, sometimes - don't eat any more of that. Though of course you thought you - you hadn't, but they thought you'd had enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way and sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
No. I think - everyone - from being able to use a knife and fork - became - quite natural to you how to use it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you have to sit up straight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes. And leave the table in a proper manner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Could you bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Not during mealtimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 And when could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 As soon as - most of you finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You had to was it till most of you had finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well you nearly all finished together you know. Well one would leave the table then the other would leave the table you see, just - just as you'd finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you have to ask to get down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No, no. Just went on your own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did all th
e family sit at the table for the meal, did you normally all sit together at the table?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes, all at one table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you always have the same places at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Very often. Very often. Sometimes there used to be a long settee you see well you'd get three on and chairs round, well - whoever sat on the settee you - you usually went to your own place. But - that seat was more of a fixture.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How was the meal served, did your mother serve it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did she use vegetable dishes or did she serve it straight from the pan?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 In both cases. Yes, both cases.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 According to when, when would she use vegetable dishes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well - probably she used to use these when she felt like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 All }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 extra}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588  washing up - isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What order were you served in, were you served in any particular order?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
No. Of course the elder ones got them first, naturally, the elder ones. And the other ones followed on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Where did the younger brothers and sisters sit before they c
ould feed themselves, Do you remember where the young ones sat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well they were often on the mat. Very often was on the mat. In front of the fire
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Who would feed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Mother. Oh she would probably - sit them on her knee and feed them from t
here. Oh there were two or three of them lined up to about three year old you see, children, baby - you baby them more or less up to three year old you see and pick it up any time. After that - after that when you got to be about six or seven you see, whe
n you could sit about - they would sit in chairs - what you say - the age of when you knew exactly what Ask for what you wanted, when would tea be ready? When would tea be ready and - and - and so forth.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 But up to then you'd either have it on the floor or on your mother's knee?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Yes. Very easy to talk to. She liked conversation you see. And of course - she got plen
ty of conversation because my dad used to tell her everything that happened. What he saw outside and what he read in the newspapers and of course he knew everything that was going on in the world. Even as regards - politics and such as that you see. Oh sh
e was quite a - she was quite well conversant on anything like that. But - through him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Did your mother show affection at all, was she an affectionate person, to you children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Average. She didn't pamper you. No. She was average like. She'd see no
 harm come to you or anything like that. Oh you couldn't say you were neglected like - not at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 If you had any worries could you share them with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Oh yes. If you cared to tell her you see. Some things of course you got into trouble you wouldn't tell.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Was your father an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Very easy. And a very good talker too. Very interesting man to talk to. And a very big reader of books he was, you see that's why he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did he show affection at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Oh yes, he - he was very good natured towards his family, you see, I mean - there were times in his life when he got a little bit irritable when - he came in and he may have been tired and he wanted you off to bed because you were making a noise and - h
e'd have you so long and then go to bed so he could read.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How did he show affection to you, your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well he would help - you in any way if you had - he would any time put his hand in his pocket when you were young then and we got a few swe
ets, by - straight away. There was - there wasn't really any way that he could help because - I mean to say as long as he looked after you, didn't hurt you, there's nothing more to do. If he had anything in his pocket and you wanted anything he used to pu
t his hand in. If you wanted a pennorth of sweets well you can get them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 If you had any worries could you share them with your father or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well yes. That's one thing you could, he'd tell you what to do. That way.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How did your parents expe
ct you to behave towards them? How had you to behave towards your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well of course they looked for all they could get when you were growing older for certain things. They'd no more to do. They probably put to you when you were younger, and the
n they hoped to see what you'd do - when you were older. Of course you'd help them considerably, especially my mother, see. The longer you went to school if you were any kind - any kind of intelligent person or intelligent child I should say, then of cour
se you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
I was asking you how your parents expected you to behave towards them and before you answered the tape ran out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 So how did they expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well - I should say like the - in the same - a si
milar amount as to they be - behaved towards us, they were very good to us, and of course anything that they wanted us to do, children in those days run messages and such as that, we were always prepared to do it, anyone, and one child was always more or 
less prepared to help you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in certain ways, you more or less answered that, you said you'd to help each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Anything else you hand to do for your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No, the next one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Any other ways in which they expected you to behave towards your brothers and sisters
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well that was too - in those days you see, a scholarship wasn't quite as good as it is today you see, and - the older one you see used to teach the younger ones anything that they thought they might know. See, such as that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well - anything in the line of - shall we say mathematics or - or anything like that. Or even writing you see, they were exci
ted about - writing and - they would set you to do so many difficult words you see with f's and e's in so that you - to see what kind of a write you would make. We used to do that as children you know. My father used to teach us that. See? And that was ho
w
 we come. There was only one thing like, I had one brother and that was crippled as I told you from - well of course he never went to school because he could never get out. And strange to say he learnt - he learnt as he laid about and sat about from the o
t
her - you know - for all they were younger than him you see, they went to school, we taught him and did everything for him. And at the finish, when he got to be fourteen or fifteen year old he was quite equally as good as what we were at fifteen and seven
t
een, for any - any ordinary scholar - schooling. Always passed it onto him, he was taught how to read and write and everything, you see, his accident occurred when he was about six or seven. And he was taught all - everything he knew, and the time was whe
n
 he grew to be a man you see as I told you about my mother, he would - he was sitting in the chair write - sometimes he used to write and - and he would read to my mother from the newspaper, anything she couldn't read she used to say - so he would read an
ything at all, and he could work out any sum do anything - any problems or any - thing, and he could do it equally as good as anyone - else of the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did they say you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 I beg your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 pardon}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did they say you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Oh yes. My father in particular. He used to have a saying - you - you've got to learn to stand up for yourself. And if ever children - used to - boys used to chase us home you see, he
 used to put the confidence into us - and he would come outside into the street where this boy was, and he would look at him, no, he said, if you - don't hold your own against him, he said, I'll thrash you back into the house. You see, he made you - what 
he was doing was made you to defend yourself instead of running about cowardly from anyone else. And he was also in my opinion improving your nervous system, at the same time you see, you weren't afraid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well - they hoped that - with the - the ordinary schooling within their power, and - and - and the money etcetera there which they couldn't do that, they lived in hope that we would live up and get a decent position in li
fe, either woman - or male you see. A suitable - to more or less make an existence in the world that was worth having.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did your parents bring you up to consider certain things important in life?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well I mean to say - hard to answer that. There was only one thing \{BLANK
\} throughout life he said there's one thing he said, you
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You don't want anyone to what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 He said you always want to avoid anyone pointing their finger at you.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What did he mean by that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well I mean to say that yo
u aren't stooping to anything where anyone could talk about you, see what I mean. You see, he this and he that, he may have gone to prison or something like that. Well he said, there's one thing, always hold your head erect. And what is more, he said, you
 
always want to try and keep on a par with anyone else. And there's one thing she did, he was a fairly good scholar were my father, he was paid for it. My mother couldn't but my father could so - so long as one of them had the necessary education, and anyt
h
ing that we wanted to know he would - do his level best to either teach you figuring or writing or reading or anything else because he was a very good reader himself, and I - eventually turned out to be a very good talker I think and a good reader myself,
 
one of the family. In fact the - most of the family was like that. One or two of course in a family of ten there's also - there's always one or two - more or less defective, they don't come forward the same way you see, but the majority of our family I th
ink as they grew up - well, to say the least of it, they didn't get to be millionaires but they learnt to live a decent life and have a decent livelihood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What did your parents think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well it's a thing that never really entered into o
ur life because my parents never swear, and they didn't really care about anyone using bad language. And if any of the children used bad language well I'm afraid it was - it would go rather bad with you if your father got to know. You were terrified your 
father got to know, you never used a wrong word because you'd go then in fear, see what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Join in what dear?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in the conversation?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
No, I don't think so, only at times. We more or less sat and - listened to what the other people said. We were not allowed see. It was a case in those days of the old saying, children should be seen and not - not heard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 If you did somethin
g your parents disapproved of what would happen? How were you punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well we thrashed as a rule. Thrashed two or three times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What with? A strap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Sometimes a piece of stick, a chain or anything like that. It was - it was one - if there 
was one thing you see you hadn't done you were told - beforehand - several hours beforehand to do a thing well supposing you more or less disobeyed it and you went out to play, well you had that when you came back. And you very often got a thrashing. Let 
me say they didn't hurt you but it was to give to understand that these things when you were told you had to do them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Who did the thrashing your father or your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 My father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did your mother ever have to thrash you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Never. I never 
knew my father - my mother ever lift a hand to any of the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How often would you say you were thrashed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well I wouldn't know as a schoolchild I should say I just - well - just when the occasion arose you see, when you were outside and you happened to get into trouble you were told to do something and you didn't do it. I should put down only occasionally.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Do you remember any particular occasion when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No, I wouldn't say that I did I mean to say all these little d
efects - that children used to get mixed up with. I mean to say one little thrashing seemed to do for him, he seemed to forget all about it. And in many instances it never occurred again. Why, because you always had the fear of me father using that - span
king again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Do you remember how you felt about being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Have I ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
How did you feel when you were punished, how did you feel about being punished?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
How do you feel about being punished, well I thought you really deserved them 
sometimes. You really deserved it but you didn't in any way - hold any malice towards your parents you see. Of course naturally used to come back to you just as you as though nothing had happened. I will say that. It used to pass away, much the same as I 
say the shkps pass in the night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Would you say you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents or did one play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No, I think it'd be a case of fifty-fifty. Although individually each o
f them I'm prepared to say that you did what was right and if they could help you in any shape or form well they both did. And if there was anything of course from the male and the female side, it would be treated - they would suggest one thing and anothe
r
 and then used to tell you what they thought between them. Now. That was the case. Well I said I think in a large family you see you probably find more trouble among children than you would in a small one you see. You see, you were each individually going
 
your own way, there was girls and boys and there wasn't a great difference in the age of any of us you see, we were all going to school together practically. And then of course - I think myself that - as a family, we got through very nicely, and of course
 
when we come to what is known perhaps as years of discretion, well - personally, as one of the family, I think I admired my father and mother for the great efforts - with so little to do. And as my mother used to say many times, she used to say, well - we
'
ve done all we could. We've fed you. You have got health. I would have liked to have educated - educated you - more than what we have been able to do, but of course we couldn't do it, but she said, at any rate, we did try and feed you and keep you in good
 health, and it's when you grew - when you grew up that you could go out into the world and we expect to hold your own and fight your own way through.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
When you had a birthday would it be different form any other day? Would you receive any present or have anything special to eat or have any friends in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Oh no. No I don't think so. I'm afraid that in - those days the - the financial department was rather low and birthdays used to come, and they just used to discuss their birthdays, and - whose - whos
e birthday it was next you see. I used to be on the twenty-sixth of - December which was of course Boxing Day of each year, and then - one of my sisters was born on the twenty-eighth, two days later you see, at a different date - of course she was - proba
bly about three or four years older than me. But when it came down to birthdays I'm afraid they just used to - pass away with same - \{BLANK\}
 whatever it is now, thirteen or fourteen, it used to pass away the same as the breeze in life. Because my people you
 see - or people like that - they may have been occasions when they bought you something for your supper or gave you something just to celebrate the occasion but there wasn't very much that they could do you see. You see, the money was not there, they wou
ld have done - my mother said they would have done more but they just simply couldn't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Can you remember anything you did with your mother and father together on Christmas Day? Do you ever remember anything about Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well we were all t
ogether on Christmas Day my dear. All together on Christmas Day, and of course we used to get little bits of presents and we thought the world of them. One thing I was very fond of, when I was a boy, and that was - what we used to call - I got a mouthorga
n. A mouthorgan. Yes. A mouthorgan and of course - various other little presents we used to get and I was also very fond of one of these - what do you call them, these things - candles in the - you know what I mean, they used to be -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Christmas tree candles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Christmas candles were in a kind of a - whatever were called those things, anyway very fond of these Christmas candles, but I used to - as near as I can tell you I used to get this here - what is the other name for a mouthorgan, there's another
 name. That man plays it - used to play it. At least we'll put it down as my - it was known to me then as a mouth organ, I used to look annually for that mouth organ.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Harmonica?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 A harmonica, that is the real name for it you know. Thank you very 
much. Well I used to look - practically three or four years before I was about fourteen you see, and - I was always very fond of it. I found in music - was - in my mind I was more or less music. For that matter - so was some of the other family. They got 
-
 they got so far up of - they got to be - when they grew up they got to be more or less - amateur actresses, my sisters. And then I lived to see the day - when the boys that I have today, I met a gentleman in later life who said to me, he said, do you kno
w
 - he come to my door - he said to me he said, are you a singer? And I just simply said to him, I said, why, whatever makes you ask that? Oh, he said, just your voice. Well, I said, I've done quite a lot of singing in my time, I said, it appears to be a n
atural gift of mine. And he turned }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 round}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
 to me and he said to me, these words, of course I was a bit older then, he said, do you know young man, he said, you're singing yourself, and he says, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 you're}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588  not only singing yourself, he says, you're singing the who
le world. He said, you were - of course that was later on in life you see. But I mean to say, when I had the - a harmonica I was always very fond of playing, and I was always singing, I once sang a song when I was a little boy - I always remember that and
 
my father sang, I was a little boy no higher than this, just a lad in short trousers and one of these like blouse things that boys used to wear, babies, and I'd be about four year old when he sang the song, and I knew the words of this song you see, and I
 
sang it right off - right through, just the one verse and he stood and looked at me like that as much as to say and I never really knew, I always wanted to know what was in his mind but I never knew. But he heard me singing you see. But of course later on
 I was told you see - that I possessed a very good voice.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Did anyone else play any musical instruments, were there any other musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Yes. Another brother mine, he - he played the piano. He had a piano and of course - my 
sister - one or two of my sisters used to sing to the piano you see. The family were more or less musical but it came on to be later in life, you see, not when we were young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well this is up to 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes, well up to 1918 of course we were just b
eginning to - find out that we more or less possessed these gifts. That they hadn't really been - brought forward, brought out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
When would it be that you had a piano, would it be before that period of after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well now let me see now - it was roun
d about 19 - 14 I should say, we had a piano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Do you ever remember making music together as a family, it sounds as though you did because somebody played the piano and your sisters sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes. I've known us all - especially when you're mentioning
, my birthday at Christmas time you see - we'll probably have a little sing song at the same time. And at the same time - at the same time we used to have what was very very common in those days and very very popular. A gramaphone. And you see the records
 of the gramaphone, well of course we used to sing to them, and I always think that that that helped to improve and bring out the voice for singing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
You say you had little presents on Christmas Day, did you have any special food on Christmas Day or did you go to church on Christmas Day or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
No. Well my mother used to like us to go to - to church you see, round about Christmas time. But - getting them all - trying to get them all dressed you see she used to get tired. She used to 
say, well I - I get so tired over Christmas, we won't bother this morning, just wouldn't bother. So of course we were more or less pleased with that. Didn't wish to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Did your parents play any games with you, any time of the year, did they play any games inside or outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Just inside door - just inside games.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What sort of games would they play with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Such as the old postman's knock, such as that you know, we had the postman's knock. Anything like that. Or hiding anything in the r
oom you see. Anything like that. Of course there wasn't - there were nothing - not very very many games, there was nothing much to do in those days. Families had to more or less amuse themselves, whether at Christmas time or for that matter, any old time.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Were there any books in the house, you say your father was a reader?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Newspapers, did you have any magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Yes. Magazines came in, and weekly - weekly magazines you see for us all to read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What sort would they be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 W
ell - there used to be - they're not there now, - there used to be a paper come from \{BLANK\}
 that was very popular, it was more like in magazine form and it was known as the Northern Weekly Gazette - Northern Weekly Gazette, and we all used to - await that
 paper you see, and particularly at Christmas, I used to like to - even when I was young, because they used to what is known as a double number at Christmas and there were all kinds of funny little stories that were true, from countries abroad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Do you
 remember your mother or father reading, you remember your father reading, your mother didn't read did she? Did they ever read aloud to you or to each other, your father did didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Do you remember a funeral in the family in those days? 
Before 1918 do you ever remember a funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Before 1918, just one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Who would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That was the - the child that died when he was ten months old you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Do you remember anything about it, what the funeral was like in those days?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well I mean to say that the funerals - there were hearse you know, the ordinary hearse. As near as I can tell you there - there was that - hearse, you see, for the coffin, and probably two car - two cabs. I - I'm not so sure about a mourning coach, I 
couldn't tell you about that. Of course I was rather young you see, I wouldn't bother about the mourning coach, there could have been a mourning coach, but at these - being a child you see it was simply put - place underneath for - the seat of one of the 
- I think it was placed underneath the seat of one of the cabs. I don't know. Of course he were only ten months old you see this child.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Do you remember who went to the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Ah now then, I - I - I think we all went. And it was in November, it
 was very cold month. I think we all went, and we all came back, but it was very very quiet you see the funerals in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Do you remember - what sort of clothes you wore for the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Pretty much what you had to go out in on the weekend
s. You had sometimes a - something a little bit better but your - your mother wouldn't allow you to abuse during the week you see. That'd be put by - put by you see for - any }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 occasions like that or any occasions}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588  at the weekend or any occasions like holiday
s or Christmas time. So as you always appeared respectable - well say if anyone came in, that sort of business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Were you ever taken out visiting neighbours, friends or relations? Did you ever go out to visit people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Only occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Who would that be, who would you go and see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
It would be someone - more or less related to us you see. And sometimes you may be in - invited out to a child's birthday you see. If there was anything it may be at our house, to our house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 When you went 
to relations who took you, who did you go with, did you all go or did your mother or your father take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
No, very often just - mother sometimes, not father. Perhaps she would take two of you you see - all depends. You see - it all depends - who was
 going and what - it was - probably used to be for a half a day or owt like that. I suppose it'd be two and - and another time she would pick other two you see. You each got your turn you see, there was no fish or one fish or other such fish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Were you ever taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
No, not particularly because in those days when - especially when we were very young you see there wasn't a great many shops.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You say you got these things through some sort of credit firm?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes, a lot of these things 
and - lot of the clothes when you were young and of course - your mother used to make little trousers you see. Such shops as you see on the high road now, and these supermarkets well - of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 course}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588  we are now living in a new world, there was nothing whatever 
then. In those days the high road as we know it now, was just a mass of cobblestones almost up to the shops.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Did you ever go out just with your father, do you ever remember going out just with your father? Without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Just occasionally.
 Only be going for a walk. Yes. It may have been to the garden you see, look round the garden you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Where was the garden, was it at Laws Terrace or when you moved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No, the garden was where -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Was it a sort of allotment you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes,
 it was - it was known - it - it used to go by the name of Tasmania Gardens. And at the bottom of the Geneva Road what is now some kind of a - reclamation depot of the corporation you see, it was all filled in slowly - with ashes you see, and it were gene
r
ally covered up then they - they kind of made a - a depot you see for reclamation, well - for the railway, I mean to say - the wagon works and such as that or - parts of - parts and - and parcel to the - the - of what they wanted for the wagons. They used
 
to be more or less you could put it down to more or less as a store yard. Well that was where our garden was, and once said to my father when we were getting about fourteen years of age - and I noticed this slag heap - it encroached and covered many garde
n
s, I said - he says, getting nearer to our garden dad. He just turned round to me when I were a boy, and he said, I don't know, he said, I think this garden will last me as long as I want it. You see what I mean, they was coming so slow and of course he w
as getting on. And whether he - he lived to see the day when he didn't, it - it finished and he got another garden somewhere else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Do you remember any outings with your parents such as Bank Holiday or anything like that, did you ever go out somewhere special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Mostly to the seaside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Where would that be, which part?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 To Redcar or Saltburn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Was this just for the day or half a day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Probably for a day.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Was this the whole family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No. Just so many of you you see. Mother w
ould take about three out. And then later on you see - well other three would go somewhere else, probably to another holiday. Used to take turns, couldn't take you all at once, a big family like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you ever go away for a proper holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 I just remember going twice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 When would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
That would be about when I was thirteen years of age. And we went and we stayed at - probably to Redcar. Redcar. Probably for about - four or five days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Who went then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well there'd be ab
out - my mother - father didn't go, poss - probably he would he be too - he - he would be at work you see, working all hours on the railway being as in - inspector then. Probably my mother and myself and - someone else, and - one or two members of - the b
oys and one of the girls you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What did you do when you were there, how did you fill your time in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Just simply by - once or twice I used to walk from - Redcar to Saltburn on the sands and - and mostly on the sand you see to play And in those d
ays used to be able to get hold of a cycle you see for so many coppers. You were allowed to cycle, to cycle about as long as ever it - so long as you took it back. And I think the cycle was - some round about threepence or sixpence a day. And then used to
 cycle round you see, and then take it back. Well I think the - the most - the time was spent mostly on and off the sands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That was your first holiday was it, when you were thirteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes. As near as I can tell you. There was no holiday - there wa
s - there was no holiday money my dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Could you tell me how you spent Saturdays in those days? Were Saturdays any different from any day when you were a schoolchild?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
When at school well I think you know - just used to pick a boyfriend outside 
you see and sometimes used to go - I used to go down to their house you see and - spend practically half a day with them. And then they would come back in and see - and comeback and see us, you were more or less - playing about you see, walking and playin
g about. You - you - go on - no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How would you spend your Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Sundays was always spent very quietly at home. Yes. I never remember - occasionally - occasionally - of course when you got older used to go to church you see. This church here. Back at - St George church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How old were you when you starred to go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well round about coming to about fourteenth year you see. Of course that was the time when I went to - I went to the confirmation classes at this church here you see 
when I was confirmed - and I was turned fourteen years of age by the then Bishop of Durham at St Hilda's church you know, perhaps you know. I was confirmed there when I was between fourteen and fifteen years of age. I received my lessons in St John's chur
ch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Had you been to church much before that or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Oh yes, we used to go fairly regular. And also Sunday school every Sunday. That was one thing we used to look forward to. To going to Sunday school at Sunday afternoon, at least one hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Y
ou said you had different clothes on Sunday, at least you tried to keep some different clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Were you allowed to play games on Sunday or did your parents think it wrong to work or play on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 My mother didn't believe in any g
ames on Sunday at all. No. And the one thing she strongly objected to was - card games with pictures. Yes. On Sundays. Strongly objected. She wouldn't allow anyone. Once we were playing one night when we were getting a little bit older with my father and 
she objected strongly. My father had to give over. Yes, he give over, he said, and it's no use playing, ma won't allow us to play with picture cards on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 I wonder why that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 I don't know, she appeared to have her own - she - she appear
ed to think in her own mind, she had a root objection because - I don't knew, it - it appeared to be a wicked game on a Sunday with playing cards, picture cards, and that's all I could tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did your mother and father attend a place of worship too
, did they go to church as well?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well - in later life, no. Many times you see when he used to be coming in on - on a Sunday morning you see and then he used to go to bed. And of course mother - being left as she was, she had the family to attend to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 So it was just you children that went to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes, it was the children, just the children always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Was it Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Church of England, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Were there any Sunday school outings that you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 None that I can remember of. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
What other social activities organised by the church did you take part in, did you take part in any other activities at the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well social activities I should put down, there used to be a kind of a schoolroom in Eas
tern Road you see, and children were allowed to go in there you see there was all kinds of little bits of games. You see to put them in in the dark night. For instance I remember quite well, quite young, and they used to put a coin in the water that was e
lectrified you see. And whoever picked this small coin out it was his. The difficulty was picking it out of this electric - electrified water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Wasn't that dangerous?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well, it wasn't in a sense - I - I - I mean to say I can't remember but - there 
must have been some form of electricity in the water because you couldn't pick it up. But who ever picked it up, it was picked up, whoever picked it up could claim it, and each child used to have a try. Sometimes it was never picked up. There was no one e
ver hurt by it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How often did you go to this schoolroom? How many nights would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well it used to be open nearly every - every - week. And that little building still standing in Eastern Road you see like kind of a - tin - it used to go by the name of Tin Castle. Tin Castle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That belonged to the church did it then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Yes, that belonged to the church. Like a small schoolroom attached to the church. And that catered you see for the children. And of course we took full advantage of it, s
ome of us, and we used to go pretty regular. You see, in the dark days there was nothing else here you see. There was nothing, of course there was - little or no danger on the roads you see, there was neither cars nor anything else. That was before even -
 
the old tramways start you know, the rail tramways. And motor cars - the only thing that there was was - bicycle and there wasn't many of them. There was really no need for - any fear of your parent anything would happen to you, there was so little traffi
c on the road. And that's where we used to go and then - come out of there somewhere about eight or - eight or half past and home and probably a cup of tea or whatever you got and - bed.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you belong to the choir at the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No, I didn't, I
 never sang in the choir. Although I could sing I never was in the choir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Did the church run any temperance club, do you remember if they had a temperance club that stopped you drinking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well they did a run a temperance club but of course I hadn
't very much to do with it, I think, we - it used to be in St John's Crescent. Not - not very far from the church, but well attended like by the way and of course there was temperance club - but I knew nothing about it but my father used to go - occasiona
lly, when he wasn't at work, he knew all about this club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 We were talking about your father going to the temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you know what he did when he was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well I wouldn't know, I think they just used to go there for con
versation. It was like a meeting for just - talk about current events or anything like that. I didn't know of any games that were played there, of course they were getting on you see, they just used to meet there - to discuss the current events and any - 
anything that might be occurring that day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you belong to any other club organised by the church at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No. None whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Were you taught to say your prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Who taught you those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 My father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you ever have family prayers all together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
No I don't remember family prayers, I only remember a family prayer once, and that was when a brother of mine, that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 crippled}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588  brother of mine, he died and the parson came in you see, and - we prayed that night. In our kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That would be out of our period though wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Yes. Yes. That's of course - I wasn't very old, just about fourteen you see when that happened. Yes. I was just about four
teen, and - I re - I well remember the - the vicar like, he was - by the name of - the Reverend Peter Meyer was his name, and of course he called to see my mother, and he came in you see and - we talked about this - you see being a cripple, he talked quit
e a long time, and then of course we all knelt in prayer in our kitchen and he knelt with us. That were my mother and father and - such as the family as - who were in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Do you remember that brother's funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Quite well. Quite well. He lived until
 he was twenty-six, but he was never out of the house. And he died when he was twenty-six, the doctor said like there was nothing he could do for him, he told my mother - if she had the money never to waste the money because no one in the world could do h
i
m any good. He also told her what came true, he said, he'll live to be a man and that is all, and he died when he was twenty-six, very strange wasn't it. Well that - that was the second funeral you see, that I attended - before I was - well when - I was a
bout fourteen years - of age I should say,. That was the second one, but the baby you see, I was only about seven when the baby was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Was this a bigger funeral, were there many people there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well - no, it - it was more as a private funeral, you s
ee, with his own people because he never knew anyone. It was just amongst ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did your father take an interest in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes, to a certain extent. Oh yes, he was a very big -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You told me he used to read -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 YES? H}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10361257\charrsid12588588 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588  used
 to read to my mother and of course he was a very big what they call Liberal in those days, well - there was the Liberal and Conservative you see, he believed in the Liberals would say in voting on this free trade, and the Conservatives went in for puttin
g this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 tariff}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
 on for their own protection. He didn't believe in it, he was always a Liberal.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Why do you think he held those views, did you ever get an idea of why we was a Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No, but he had strong views of his own, of course me being so yo
ung I wasn't really interested, but he had strong views of his own, he didn't seem to think - the protection - was - the money that we earned over here - he didn't see there was any sense in taxing the goods what was coming into this country, that we had 
to purchase on top. He thought they wouldn't have been so dear - so dear to purchase had that tax not been there for entrance, now you see, that was what he based his politics on in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How about your mother, did she take an interest in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No, just followed my father. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 A lot of the wives did that didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 So she was a Liberal too then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 She was a Liberal too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Do you remember your father or mother voting in a general election bef
ore 1919, I think women had the vote in 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Do you remember them voting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Remember my father voting? Yes. He used to vote in every one - in Darlington, he even voted for a man that came here, he was supposed to be a \{BLANK\} 
that got in through - he - he threw - a Conservative member who had been sitting for twenty-two years, and he was an Austrian, you see, and he came over here. And he had such a grip on the people - you see, he was talking, you see, of course as - as his }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 opponent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
 used to say - fellow countryman, but he could - my father used to say, he couldn't say fellow countrymen but he had a very nice way of saying, ladies and gentlemen, you see what I mean. And he eventually - when the poll was declared they were quite 
sure you see the Conservative would turn up - and to everyone's surprise and \{BLANK\}
 of the country my father did vote for the Liberal that beat him, I will say that, and he beat the - the Conservative by either twenty-nine or thirty-two votes. Yes. Very c
lose indeed. That was when I was about fifteen years of age, of course I was working then you see. I saw the poll declared that night from the Town Hall, and everybody was amazed, absolutely amazed and staggered.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 So your father always voted Liberal then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 He was a Liberal right 'til the very end.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Do you remember when your mother actually went to vote, do you remember her voting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Yes, she used to and put her cross, one of her - one of her daughters used to go with her you see. You see a
nd - oh she could put the cross you know, she only - used to put her glass on - glasses on and - they used to point at the name you see and she would probably put the cross. And she always voted Liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 In some places at that time men felt they riske
d losing their job or their house if they voted differently from their employers. Do you know if your father felt himself under that kind of pressure, to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That could have been. It was very very general in those days. And t
hat's why some people would not discuss politics. You know that. And - they would on no consideration because in many instances people who believed that they voted the other side that they were dismissed from their - from - from - from the job and the pos
i
tion they have. Therefore they kept it secret, and - my father once said to someone one day, well - and he said, yes, he said, we have a right, we have the vote and we're going to cast it, but, he said, we always like to believe that - that vote is secret
, and my cross is secret. See what I mean. You'll probably get that wherever you've been, majority.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
So do you think your father felt himself under any kind of pressure at all or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No, I don't think so, not the position he held, but still of co
urse - as things was so bad and - if a person - if a man - we'll say was to lose his position in those days it was a very very serious matter for a man with a family, seeing that in those days there was neither - sick benefit nor any kind of benefit, ther
e
 was no such thing as unemployment benefit, and - of course that worried greatly upon his mind when he began to do anything like that. If a cross was going to run his life, well he might just as well have ab - abstained from crossing, and remained neutral
. Nowever he used to turn round and say, well - the vote is secret and - wherever we put our cross, he said, it's our business, and it remains so. I've heard him say that many time. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Was he a member of a political party, was he a member of the Liberals or not?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No, no. No, he just - used to cast his vote.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Do you remember him working for one of the parties at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Or your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did he take part in any political activity other than at election time?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
No I think not. He just used to be interested in the candidate or a certain - he hoped that his man got in, of course we knew where he put his vote you know. But of course - then again, being younger - we weren't just as interested then you
 see, we used - we used to like to see our man win and - and after that well - it just passed away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their time? How did your parents spend their free time if they had any, I don't suppose your mother had much did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
She hadn't much but used to occasionally go to a place of amusement together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What sort of a place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well there was really like only theatres in those days, there was no pictures you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 They occasionally went to the theatre then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Just occasionally went out, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Just your mother and father together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Yes, they would go together, just them, of course - we would be - someone would be prepared to look after the younger children you see until such times as they returned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Anywhere else you remember them going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
They used to go for - day trips you see - we'll say when he used to get - days off from the railroad, sometimes go away somewhere for the day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Of course you'd get cheap tickets too wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Yes, he used to have passes you see. And he used to probably go - difference places York anyway where they used to go but - they would travel there and back for nothing, well I suppose - and apart from that they used to travel
 - half of the single fare for what they call a privilege ticket. Half of a single fare you see brought them back. On occasion and they used to go just out. Sometimes they'd see - probably my mother's sister you see just for a day wherever it might be.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did your mother have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No. I think her life and soul was spent with the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself without your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 I wouldn't say so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 She just went with him to the theatre or for a visit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
When did your father get home from work in the evenings, he was on shifts wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well his time - his time used to vary you see then. Because he used to start at different times and you know any time - any time at - r
ound the clock. And in those days you see they very often put in long days, I've once heard my mother say he was once away three days, before he got back. And of course in those days there - there was no such things as a - as a forty hour week you see, no
thing like that. They had to come back, get back as soon as ever they could. And my mother never knew when to expect him until he walked in any time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How many evenings a week would he be able to spend at home do you think?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well, it all depend you
 see - if - if he could get him by about teatime or just turned six o'clock. But I will say my father - he never seemed to go out a lot, he always used to remain in with my mother and the family. Not one of these men that got dressed and away out you see,
 and some - to the public house or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did he ever go to any club or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
No. No, he just used to get - get the paper, get his slippers on and sit over the fire and until -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Your father sounds a nice man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 He was very n
ice that way. And there was nothing he wouldn't try to - to show us you see. He tried to show us, as I told you, every mortal thing, even - I told you before - even showed the girls how to plait their hair you see. And how would we put clothes on you see,
 anything, for the greatest help.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did your father take part in any sport at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
No, I don't think so. He was interested that was all. He would occasionally, I only remember him but occasionally got to a - a football match but - it was on a Good
 Friday near - as near as I can tell you, and - one of the participants, one of the teams would be one belonging to the railway where he worked you see. But that only occurred probably each Good Friday, and as far as I know he never went any more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did
 he attend the races, you told me that little story he used to tell you, did he attend the races when he was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
He did not my dear. All that occurred when he was single man. It occurred right in the last cen - century when he was a single young
 man. But of course he was always interested in following through same as anyone might be follow football. He was just as interested in - in a big race coming along, and he would - he would try and find the winner you see, and then it - gradually graduall
y we used to do it and we used to try and find the winner, that was all we used to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did he ever bet at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
I never remember him, no. Well I must say - he hadn't the money. If he'd had - if he'd taken the money for that and lost it then I'm afraid the household, wife and children must have suffered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Did your father or mother belong to any savings cubs, any boot clubs, sick clubs, funeral clubs or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 He was only in a sort - in one sick club as near as I can tell you. 
That was for - drawing sick benefit you see when he was ill, but I can't just tell you which one it was, I think it was the - something like the Hearts of Oak or something like that but I - I'm not quite sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How did you get on with your brothers and
 sisters, you got on reasonably well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 Quite}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588  well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Was there one you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 I think that always happens in a family my dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Who would be the one that you were closest to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 The one that was - next to me. 
About four years older, the one I told you - was - born two days after I was, twenty-sixth of December, she was born - of course four years previous on the twenty-eighth. Well I think that was my favourite sister because she was very - she never married a
n
d she was always - very easy and very shy. She would never pass you by if she thought she wanted you - if she thought you wanted anything and she could help - you, she'd do it. There is always someone in the family you see that you stick to, that is - at 
l
east I think so, there's always one member of the family - that you appear to stick to the most, you appear to think more about them for something or some reason about them, - that they're probably isn't about the others. The others'll be quite all right,
 but there's something ex - extra - extra special about this person, that you think you like them the best.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 As a child who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 As a child who I used to play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Your brothers or sisters or neighbours children or both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Neighbours children. Yes. Very fond of a game of football in the season you see, we used to go - I used to play with the school too. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Where did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
We used to play - at the place I think up - up here called Brankin Moor. I can't remember what they call it, it's somewhere up here - on - Yarm Road. Somewhere where these houses are you know, Kensington Gardens and all round there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Where else did you play with neighbours children when you weren't playing proper football?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Sometim
es used to go down to their - their residence you see and spend a half a day with them just playing about or - going anywhere, going to the park. The park was the main place where we used to go you see. The parks. If we weren't playing we were watching ot
h
er people - other children you see. And then of course you came back, a long way walk and - it used to be a long walk back home and be all tired when you got home and go for your tea. And that's - that's well of course there wasn't very much done after th
at. The evening was more or less spent - indoors.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Do you remember any games that you played apart from football, any games you played just with children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well there used to be - little - little ball games where we used to run about, that's all an
d handball they used to call it, see, there was no other - no other games particularly. There used to be - called handball and run for the ball just round the corners of the streets, and if you failed to get the ball well of course the next one went in, a
nd that's about the only thing we ever knew. Handball and football.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well to a certain extent. But - ma used to keep coming out, you see, to see if you were all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Were you free to play with
 anyone you pleased or did your parents discourage you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 could}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
 do with who you liked, As long as there was some - someone that you knew they were mostly neighbours you see in those days my dear, people were more 
friendly more neighbourly and more friendly than I'm afraid I can say today. And you see - neighbours - used to run practically the whole length of the terrace, see, and you used to play with them all. One way and another, some of them used to keep pigeon
s used to go and watch them, well you see - there was nothing else to do, you found great interest in watching those. If you weren't playing yourself you were watching someone else - some - some other child's activities.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you belong to any youth organisations at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Never. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Did you have any hobbies then, did you keep any pets or collect anything, do gardening, you did do gardening didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well it was garden you see was my father's my - main hobby. You see, it was him that tau
ght me quite a lot about the garden. And whenever he went to the garden when he was off, even when it was growing we used to just walk down to the garden same as they do and walk to see how things were going on. After they'd been - well say after they wer
e set.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you keep any pets when you were a schoolboy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well more or less the family pets. We used to have - two cats. And - and one dog
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did they get on all right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Quite. They were very fond.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you ever go fishing at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Sometimes but - we used to do it - have an ordinary childs net you know. The only time we used to go fishing was for these little minnow things see, it was just more or less fun but we used to think it was a great feat to get some - get them in a - put th
e
m in a pound jar with string on and take them back home again and water in. See there was not fishing for any - any big fish, just in the ordinary pond. And in the park pool you see, the small lakes in the park. In fact they do that to this day children. 
Yes, well we did that. But that was as far as the fishing went. And I was never a fisherman when I grew up, I didn't seem as though I had the time or the patience to go fishing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You've got to be very patient haven't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you ever go for walks, you used to go for walks didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
That's one of my chief hobbies. And when I grew older it was one-of my chief hobbies on a Sunday night. Got for a nice long walk - with - someone, just another person how know, walking round - on summ
ers nights. Walk three or four miles you know right the way around, sometimes more. I was always a great walker that way. As I grew older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you have a bicycle when you were a schoolboy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 I had one - I hadn't one when I was a schoolboy. I would
 have liked one but unfortunately - we couldn't afford that, I'll put it that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
When you went for walks as a schoolchild who did you go with, was it with your family or with a friend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Sometimes just - an ordinary fam - neighbour you see. You 
more or less played up with two or three neighbours children you see and either one or the other you used you see you passed your time with day by day. In one way or another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you take part in any sports, you said you played football, any other spo
rts did you take part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Yes, I used to be a runner. Used to run for the school, I was - it was the run for the school you see. I was fairly good, I was - I was particularly fast at - at one hundred yards or anything like that you see, what is calle
d the sprint, and I took some beating at a hundred yards, and I did love running that way. But for - running a distance like a mile I'm afraid that - I hadn't the stamina somebody - I was much better you see, I was much faster at - at the hundred yard spr
int and that's what I used to stick to, just an ordinary sprint. And went on like that right up to the time - I left school, at the same time right up to the time I left school I played football for the school, and then of course after that well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you ever go to any theatres or concerts or music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
I just used to go to - the pictures when they first - yes, the pictures did start you see before we left school, and I used to go - to the pictures, probably once a week, there used to be - no c
hange at the pictures, and of course it used to be so cheap. There used to be what was known as complimentary ticket, and you could get in, a child could get in for one penny.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You used to go about once a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 And used to go to the pictures about once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 But not to theatres or music hall that you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
No no. Very rare I went to the theatre, it was only at Christmas time, I've seen me go to the theatre Christmas time - when I was a boy about fourteen years of age, to see a pa
ntomime you see. Now that's when I found out - when I was about fourteen was Cinderella. That's when I was exactly fourteen. That's a bit since. And that was the Darlington Theatre Royal. And I was so sorry for Cinders I wanted to go on the - I wanted to 
go on the platform you know, you know. I was only a boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Were your parents able to give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well it used to run to penny I think. I thought we - we were very rich, to get one penny per week. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What did you spend your pocket money on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Just - very often a few sweets. But I very often on a Saturday morning I had to clean the - clean all the knives and spoons and forks before I got it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You'd got to earn it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Aye, you'd got to earn that penny, just by cle
aning the knives and forks you see and spoons. And then of course when you did that you got the penny and you were free to go out. And spend it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You'd feel very rich then wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes. Would - we did feel rich with a penny, aye. No doubt about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after her house or family, any relations, friends or neighbours at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 If - if anyone - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 an}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
 - anything happened in the house you see - but - they needed anyone - we'll say a little bit of
 a accident or - or one of the children was ill, any of the neighbours would come in. And of course, they would come in if your mother was bad you see. And they would try and see - see my mother and see what they could do to help.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 In what ways would they help, what would they do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well they would - do - do the housework, help to do the housework or - get any of the food in you see that the children couldn't do it. Oh I mean to say the neighbours in those days they were very very helpful to - you know, the older people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
If your mother was ill or confined to bed how did she manage? What happened when one your younger brothers or sisters was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Were born you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How did she manage when she was ill or confined to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 When s
he was confined to bed, well of course - she used - she used to know a very old lady friend that was older than herself, she was a midwife and she used to come up - come over at any time that she wanted, and her sister. Had her so many hours per day, see,
 
then go back. She used to come and see her - that the form was running right. Anything she could do for my mother she was incapable getting up or doing for herself, she would do all she could for her this old lady and then of course she would go away. Wel
l of course in a few days my mother was probably getting back onto her feet again. You see what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Did your parents have any relatives living nearby? Where were your nearest relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well my father'd got brothers in the town like. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Were they the only ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Yes, my father, I don't know my mother used to - she hadn't many relatives round the town but she had - a few up by the on the Brompton Road, Catterwick and Northallerton. But of course - in those days }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 somehow}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588  they never u
sed to go to meet them, and my father you see, well of course when he was getting older - and they never bothered with their brothers unless something was needed they went - they would probably go to a funeral or something like that, they wouldn't like th
at - they wouldn't desert after all. They never used to visit each other, you see what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
How much did you see of your father's relatives in the town, did you see them much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Just occasionally - used to see them. I mean to say, my father was 
- brother's family you see, you sometimes meet them probably for a talk, just have an occasional word and that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You didn't actually visit?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No. No visiting at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did your parents have any friends, any special friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 I woul
dn't say so, not in the town. There were more or less friends all round them you see, the neighbours were their friends. And as - as far - as far as any special friends well - as near as I can tell you, I think they were pretty much neighbourly that far.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did your mother and father share the same friends, neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Oh yes, just the same. Just the same. In many instances each of the neighbours worked on the same place - the railway, as him. And of course they used to - my mother used probably go 
to their house you see for a while and - she would come and see my mother you see, something like that, just for a short - a little bit of a - discussion or anything like that. Just for a change have a little talk about -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did your father have friends of his own as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well, no, you see, he was a man that didn't really go out, he - when - when he got on and we were - of course we were only really young then, he used to confine himself just to his work and to spending his time in the house. He wo
uld sit down and play any games with us you know, as children. Such as little games you do sit down and have a game with anyone well same as draughts and - game of draughts or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 dominoes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588  or anything like that. But I never remembered him ever coming home and 
going out. About - the other people you see, he always spent his time with my mother and his family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 The friends were the neighbours then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You say they came into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How often would neighbours come into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Just occasionally. They used often to talk a - on their doorsteps you see. But I will say like they were very friendly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Would - they be offered anything to eat or drink when they came in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Sometimes, a cup of tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Would that be on any particular day or occasion?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
No. No, probably just be making a cup of tea or anything like that, you know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Would you say that the neighbours invited in were your mother's friends or your father's friends or friends of both of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Friends of both I should say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did they just call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That's right. Especially the nearest neighbours you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You say occasionally your parents visited neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 People often te
ll us that in those days they made their own amusements, what do you think your parents did when they got together with their neighbours, did they ever make music or play games or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No I don't think they did, they would probably go 
to a concert party you see, all the neighbours may go to some kind of a concert party if there's anything on, in any of the schoolrooms or the church hall or sometimes - in any hall in the town, they would probably go and see something particular. Then yo
u see they would all go but they wouldn't - they wouldn't go you see because they were neighbours, they were going because - and they knew each other you see when they got these, they were more or less - they weren't - with strangers, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Many peo
ple divide society into different social groups or classes. In that time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one class and some to another? Could you tell me what the different ones were? What sort of social classes were there in those d
ays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
I think there was a - distinct difference between working classes and - and the middle class people in those days, I used to think so. And I think it was very pronounced. If you see what I mean. It was a - it was a case of - could you put it down
 on a - some form of class distinction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What class would you say you belonged to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well - the general working class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What sort of people belonged to the same sort of class as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 People that you worked with and people that yo
u met every day on the streets.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What sort of people belonged to the middle class that you mentioned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
I should say the people who - in control of certain jobs and business people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What sort of jobs would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well I mean to say an
yone that was more or less - the chargehand of any particular job you see. Or the manager anything like that. But it - I don't think it was happening in every case you know, sometimes - they lined up alongside - I couldn't say they were all alike that way
.
 There was some of these people like - I think the further you got up - you fur - the further you got up for - to the superintendant line of the place well they were the worst - the - the more they appeared to treat you as a human being. See what I mean? 
Yes. Yes. But the farther - the farther you got up you seemed to think more of the gentleman at the top than you did half way. Yes, that's quite true.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Can you remember ever being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No. I wouldn't say so. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Were you ever told to touch your cap or show respect in some way to any body?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 We were taught that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Who did you have to show respect to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Show respect to a lady as you pass by, or a school master or sc
hool teacher, or any person like that you know who was slightly above you. You had to recognize your schoolteacher. Or a lady too you see, you were supposed to raise your cap even to a neighbour passing. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Was there anyone you called sir or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Just these people that - masters and - and schoolteachers you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Do you ever remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these ways, did anyone ever touch their cap to your parents or call them sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well not in 
that respect but I - I've known them respect them by words - and deed. And their deeds you see, yes. They respect them by - we'll say talking about them, very nice man that \{BLANK\} you see, they would respect him by word.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 In this area, in the town or 
this part of the town who were considered the most important people at that time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
I think the most important people then - much more so now was the - was the rulers of the town, the Council Chamber. As near as I can tell.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you come into contact with them at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Just later in life you see. Just later in life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Why do you think they were considered important, the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 councillors}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588  in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well - for some reason or another children seemed to think like that they belonged to the police.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 I wonder why that connected?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
You know, they seemed - I couldn't explain exactly what it was you know, you were always afraid of the policeman, and if anyone talked about the council or the alderman, well you thought it was - it was some
body like just as powerful as the police. And that was as far as your mind went, you never bothered any further you know, except that you knew that these were a great power in the town - in the town all around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Was there anybody else that you thought of as being important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You told me that in the district where you lived the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 councillors}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
 were important, were there any other important people in the district that you can think of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Let me see. No, I wouldn't call anyone important, I mean to say 
the council chambers - it appeared to me to be about the - the most important people there were. And the doctors you see, in those days of course there was no national health insurance and the doctor of course was your gentleman doctor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What about the shopkeepers, who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Who?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 The shopkeepers, who did - they have for friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
The shopkeepers? Well - I don't know, I think they were a very quiet set of people, I don't think they went anywhere very much, and I don't t
hink they blended one with another as far as I can remember, you see, they were more or less - they would make up with the ordinary people, see what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
And what about the clergy, who would they have with friends, did they clergy mix with the people?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
The clergy, yes, the clergy in those days which I don't now of it now, the clergy used to visit the parishioners, you see, when I was young I mean. You see, when I was going to school and - and after that. And as I told you you see that - I atte
nded the confirmation classes as this particular church, St John's where I was baptized and then of course after the classes I was confirmed at St Hilda's church by the then Bishop of Durham.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 So you say the clergy were friendly with everybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 They were very friendly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How about the teachers, who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
The teachers? Well I couldn't tell you that, I should say that they more or less associated with themselves, but only in a very small way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How about the farmers, who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
The farmers? Well I don't think I can say anything about the farmers apart from them coming into the town - and selling their goods and returning. I couldn't tell you anything whatever what the farmers did or their - associations with other people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What about the employers, who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
The employers I think you know they more or less - a - I should say they mingled with employers from - from other - various - what should I say, factories or institutions, wherever they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 With their own kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 With their own kind, put it down that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
What sort of people would you say went to church and what sort went to chapel, was there any difference between the people that went to church and chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well - I should say that the church - well in my opinion, I - going right through - of course they were all - very good friends at each, would say the church people and the chapel people among themselves were all very good friends. But someho
w - I think more or less there was a certain class went to the churches - they would in my opinion, whether I'm right or wrong - be prepared to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 stand slightly}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588  aloof from the others, and I thought - I always think that they thought churches was - what I sho
uld say - somewhere above such as the ordinary the chapels, the Wesleyans and such as that. The church people thought they were more or less - well what should I say, the elite - of the churchgoers.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What sort of people would you say went to chapel then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well the people that went to chapel were indeed very very friendly. I mean to say they all mixed together as though they were going to a party. That was one vast difference in the church. You see, it's - a lot of people that at tended the church 
- I think most of - a lot of them used to more or less stand aloof from the others. Why I couldn't tell you but - of course you'll find these classes wherever you go even now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same stand
ard of living or would you say there were different groups even within the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well I think you know that some people - some workers - would be better than - better than the other class of people for one reason you see, some people - were 
never placed redundant, they always appeared, although they hadn't big wages, they always appeared - in a what you might term a secure job, it was security although it was a small living. And you see, the railway in those days, they didn't pay much - much
 money in my father's time, but still at the same time - I can well remember my }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 mother saying}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 , I will tell you this like, that - they were weigh - they were weighing children at school. And I was one that was weighed amongst my number and of course I never 
heard anything said but I heard my mother say later - that they said - that they'd said to me but I don't seem - seem to remember it, of course it had been said, they'd asked me where my father - my father worked. So I told them. And the reason why they a
sked was that I was - so - physically fit, you see, and - plenty of flesh on you, put it that way, physically fit - and big for my age, as though I wasn't in need, I wasn't lacking in any food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Was there a difference in the way people lived even within
 the working class? Would you say that some didn't have such a good standard of living or some had a better standard of living than others in the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well I used to say to myself there's a lot of unemployment in those days and I think the 
person, the man that was working would be slightly - better off than the per - than the person that was continually out of work looking for work. I think the money that they had going in - particularly I say this because there was no unemployment benefit,
 
there was no national assistance, and of course there was only what was known as the Board of Guardians. And what anybody got there - I'm afraid wasn't a great deal in those days I think - I don't think they ever got any money, they did - but it was mostl
y groceries, you see, for the family. A small amount of groceries, and not too many at that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Do you think that any one group in the working class felt itself superior to the rest?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No I don't think so unless someone - it would be in the mind of s
ome folk - they may have had a slightly better job than someone else and they appeared to think they were slightly above them but - taking all in all I think the working class was more or less on a par.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Were some families thought of as rough and some others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Yes, well of course - the same as today, but - but - not so bad as today, not so severe - as these - child delinquents. You see, there used to - you - there used to be a - a rough class of children in those days, and then there
 was a class of people that just used - the children just used to play ordinary. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Where would these rough ones come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well they would come from what I might term the rough end of the town you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Where was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 I would call that Albert Hill in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Do you remember a distinction of this kind, that's rough and respectable, between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Just ask that again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Do you remember a distinction of this kind, that's rough and respectable, between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Could possible - could possibly be - that the craftsman you see was - in a better position in life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You say there might have been a distinction of this kind a bit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 A little bit, but not a lot. I think the childr
en those days were - pretty much - of a muchness. I should say that. Because where it is - there wasn't such a great deal to choose you see for children. There was neither pictures - there was no electricity, there was no cars, there was nothing on the ro
ad, in those days you see - there wasn't - there wasn't such a thing as known as a tarmac road, they were known as the old iron roads, and you see this road that used to come up here used to be pretty similar to an iron road in the country. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You sa
id that sometimes the craftsmen were very friendly with the labourers, that they got a friendship between them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Oh yes, they did. Yes. Particularly those that - worked in the same shop you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did your mother and father have the same attitude 
to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
No, I don't think so, I think in those days the people - I'm taking the people that was living surrounding us. They were very very good natured and very helpful people, and any - anyone anywhere round needed assistance
 - any of them would go. Whether it was my mother or whoever it may be - in the nearby district that they knew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
How about people in different classes, did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in any sort of class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No, I don't 
think so apart from of course there were some people you see held good positions and - perhaps it passed through my mother's mind you see that we - we hadn't been so fortunate as those you see, they could go about - they could go to church you see. They c
o
uld go to church from there in silk hats you see, you see the difference, well there was no silk hat to ordinary working people. And of course these people were all known. But still they were very nice people really. They didn't - they didn't anyway - tur
n round and snub the people who were below them because in many cases - they employed these people - now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
You say your mother would feel she belonged to the working class, could this be because she was thinking of her parents or your father's work or t
he house or what? Or her own job that she'd had. Why would your mother put herself in the working class, what would be the reason for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well I think that would be with her - the way she was brought up you see, she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 brought up}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588  more or less - in
 - in an ordinary - very ordinary working class people, of course most of them - were then, and there seemed such little possibility of rising, getting out of it, that they were quite content to remain as they were. And all the people that ever she knew h
er relatives and everyone whatever I knew, she put - pretty much on a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 part with}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588  each other. But they were - there's one thing they were always, they were always prepared to try to keep the children tidy, and give them as much education and help them as ever
 - as much as ever they could for the benefit - when the years passed by, that they would be able to look after themselves, and in that - I think that my mother and father did very well because our family did - fairly well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Was it possible to move fro
m one class to another, do you remember anyone who did, who sort of moved up the social scale?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
I don't remember anyone particular, not moving out of - what I would call the working habitat to - reaching - a higher position in any shape or form. I thi
nk everyone was pretty much of a muchness right through, if anyone did - it was a very isolated case of which probably I would forget.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady? I think you said the doctors were didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Yes. The doctors were always classed - and we always regarded them, because you see in those days there were no motor cars - and they used to come round you see with a coachman very often, in an open carriage in fine weather, therefore he was c
lassed more or less as a gentleman doctor. And of course they put very much faith in the doctor that used to come in those days because I remember one - he lived in Darlington, we'd a very good doctor and he always came in an open carriage and I think his
 name was Doctor Manson, that was the one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Anyone else you'd say was described as a real gentleman or a real lady?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Just the people who - probably - the directors or the bosses where - your own people worked. They probably lived somewhere around you you see, not in that quarter but somewhere within distance of you. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
And why do you think that was? Why would they have been thought of as being gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well you see they would live in what you might call a - a better cl
ass quarter of the town, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Which were the better areas of the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well I should say that - South End, South End, all along South end Avenue. And the West End. And the West End. And that's where they used to - of course most of these houses 
I'm speaking about now my dear, they're all used - they're all finished and done with, and they're taken over by such as these great big firms you see. Well - same as the people that's - that's building the Town Hall of Darlington. They took over a lot of
 these houses, which in those days - were - were the homes of these people - who were the employers of the town. And in the West End of course there was Pierremont - Pierremont Hall where the Pease's lived, Henry Pease lived there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 A policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
YES? HE WAS - he used to - he used to take - great delight in chasing us around the back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What did you think of him?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well - we had a certain fear of him but so
mehow or other - he - he just used to chase us round and he was after any further trouble. And it was very very rare that he - he ever took any action against you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 When you were naughty did your mother ever say, I'll call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes. Very 
often. Always going to bring someone in you know, to kind of more or less - bring some fear into your mind, that was one thing they used to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
How do you think the policeman treated the people, how on the whole did he treat the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well I t
hink in those days - they were more like - more neighbourly than what they are today. Of course I'm not saying anything about the police today you know, but - they got to know you so well they used to address people as - Mr Lawson and - but these days the
y're - what - they don't do it now, they just walk around here - more abrupt you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you see anything of the landlord at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Just when he came for the rent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How did you fee
l about him as a landlord, what was your reaction to him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well I just seemed to think that he was a man that used to come for the money so we could live in the house. And then when he went away of course he was forgotten and the next time when he came probably we'd out playing so -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Do you remember feeling your parents had to struggle to make ends meet, you told me they had hadn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Oh yes, there was times when - there was times when they were - they were very hard pressed. 
Of course - I will say this like, there was once - my mother - of course this - this is quite true you see, my mother was once - hard up to pay the - pay the rates you see and in those days a man used to come round, and of course I never knew, my mother t
o
ld me later, we were children you see, and shame about this because he said, I'm sorry Mrs Lawson, there - there was a very beautiful sideboard all hand painted from my mother, beautiful sideboard it was, black. Black oak you see. And he came round and he
 
said, I'm afraid, he said, you know, I'm sent to do this, it's not my fault. And he had a little - a little - tag you see, like cardboard - and it with a - like string or - elastic to it, and he dropped it be - he said, I'll just drop it behind the sidebo
ard so as no one can see it. Those rates were paid and he come and took it away.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Were they going to take the sideboard away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 And they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 If they hadn't paid their rates?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes. That - that sideboard was doomed I'm afraid. Because he 
put this disc behind you see. I don't know what was under this, because I was pretty young you see. I always remember that, however - money was got and - and the rates were paid and that's the only occasion - that I ever knew that my mother was - exceptin
g
 - when it came to the end of the week of course - with only one worker, she had to contrive - to con - to make meals sufficient until such times - as - the wage packet came in you know. And in that I mean she was very successful and when I come to look a
t myself today at my age - I think they done remarkably well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
How did you feel about your parents having to struggle, do you remember feeling anything about it yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
But somehow or other we - we didn't seem to know anything other you know. Up
 to then we hadn't seen that there was something better. That's the way it was. We didn't know there was anything really better be - in the family we seemed to think that that was more or less - the line of life we had to follow. And you could only - you 
could only hope for something better next day for your meals, but as far as other - but as far as the money was coming from we had no idea like of course, we didn't go all that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What difference did it make to the family when your father was ill or 
out of work? Was your father ever ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
He was ill or out of work, no he was very very fortunate, he was only off for a - be for a day or so. He - he never had any length of time - you know, illness in bed. My father was very very fortu
nate with his family. Of course later in life when we were all grown up of course he was in bed, but - at the time when the children were there he was very fortunate. And of course he looked after himself, he didn't abuse himself, drinking or anything els
e. As my mother used to say he was very fond of bread, well I said, take a lot of bread to kill him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you ever get any help from the Guardians or the parish or any charity?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Never remember it. No. Not as children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 When there was someone i
n the district whom the people disapproved of very strongly, was there any special way in which they showed it, do you remember anyone being made to leave by rough music, that's banging on pans and telling them to get out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Oh yes, I - I've known that
 but - it - in - in - in - in some ways - in some ways, when somebody - they've been - undesirable, probably in the houses, not in - they didn't belong there and they were undesirable, and - the neighbours made every effort - to help this person you see, 
the person who was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 suffering}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
, and - they would help every - they would make every - what should I say - every assistance to try to get this person out of the house, even so far as going to the police. I once saw that done with my mother her neighbour next door.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Because she had a rotten neighbour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Because they were - no, some - somebody went to stay there, and they didn't wish them you see. Anyway they got the police to put them out but that's a lot of years since, I was quite young. That was down 
here. And my mother went up to a person now and said, what do you think about this person now? And they were taking her away inside the coach or whatever it was, she must have been bad. Well that's the only isolated occasion that I can tell you - anything
. People who were not desired and they've had to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
You don't remember the neighbours themselves ever sort of banging on pans and telling them to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
No. No, everything was very peaceful that way. I never remembered the neighbours that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How old were you when you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
I went to school - I went to school twice really, I - I went - to Beaumont Street, that's down Neasham when I was three years of age and - and then - a child or something hit me you see and - and then my mot
her refused to sent me anymore that age until - I forget whether it wasn't - five year old when you were allowed to go. And then I commenced at a school called St John's school along here, its now closed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You were only three when you first stated at Beaumont Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 When I first started.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you do a full day then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes, but it was more like a nursery you know than - in the classroom.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What time would you go in the morning and what time would you come back?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well I think we we
re taken down you see I think it was somewhere about - a quarter to nine, I think we got there about nine o'clock as near as I can tell you. And then I think we come away somewhere about - half past three or a quarter to four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What kind of a school was it, was it a church school or a board school?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Church of England school. Church of England school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Was it for boys or girls or a mixed school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Mixed. Mixed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How did you get to school, you say someone took you, did you walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Wel
l I walked really, we - we'd to - we used to just walk very slowly. And then at the finish I used to go down with the children you see, was - there was no danger much of any traffic in those days you see. We used to walk down and - and in, but I can't - I
 cannot remember from three year old what we were doing, my mother told me that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Have you any idea how long it would take you when you were three year old to get to Beautmont Street from here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 I should say somewhere in the region of about
 half an hour or forty minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 And your mother went with you to begin with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
You say you had your midday meal at school, what sort of a meal did you have if you didn't come home for your meal, at Beautmont Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well I can't re
member what we were doing at - perhaps we got something at school do you see but I cannot remember back to three. You'll have to come back to my next school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
What did you think of the school when you were at Beaumont Street, have you any recollection of it, did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well - I mean to say there were a lot of like pupil teachers as near as I could tell you for the children, it was more like a nursery I should say. And the only thing that you had to do was - more or less be in the classroom, I think you were }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 playing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
 more than anything else you see, you couldn't possibly learn very much at three - at three years of age, three to four.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Do you remember anything about the teachers, whether you liked them or not?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well I th
ought the teachers were very nice, they were - they were only very young you know but they were very very capable and very very patient in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 So on the whole would you say you liked or disliked that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 I can - only say that I - lik
ed every moment of it, as a child of that age, as far as I can remember back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life, manners, tidiness, punctuality or ways of speaking, you think it was just a play school do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well I 
think everything - that you've said there, everything there was more or less included you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You think they did all that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes. More or less included.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Do you remember what happened there if the children did anything the teachers disapproved of, what would happen then? How did they punish the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
I don't think - they didn't really punish them, they more used to stand somewhere out behind the class you see with their back to the class, something like that. That's about the only thing they used to do with children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Do you know for what sort of offences you'd get standing out at the front?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well for misbehaving yourself you know and being young - just misbehaving ourself in the class - used to bring you out for - almost next to nothing, trying to make you keep quiet while they talk to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did the girls get the same sort of treatment as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
I should say so, yes. It was a school that was very popular right through even to the older ones later on after I came away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork, did they ever ask you what you did there, I don't suppose you remember that do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
No, can't remember that. It was just - just to put that very plainly I think - we shouldn't have gone
 to school but - I think my mother sent us there more or less - out of the way while she could work. And those people - those young teachers just used to - I remember quite well just sitting. Just sitting you know and looking round and - but I couldn't im
agine what the teacher was talking about, it wasn't very much, it was just something probably to interest you, or a little bit of singing, anything like that. Just to keep you quiet.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Would the children come from similar types of home to your own or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Mostly, yes. I should say mostly - well practically all one class you see, the working class only.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Did the teachers single out any children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No, I wouldn't say so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Do you remember if there we
re any gangs or groups in the school or any children who were left out of things at that early school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
No, I don't think so, I think they were all more or less very friendly and popular with each other as all children, and when they used to go out in
 the playground you see for half hour or whatever it was to play, they always used to play about you see, there was - there was never any nonsense and never any quarrelling which they don't want.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Now we're back to the school you went to when you were five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What time did you go in the morning then, would it be near to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well it was near to us you see, we could practically get there - in a matter of a few minutes, well say for - ten minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Just walk it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What time did school finish then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 We used to start I think at nine o'clock and we finished at - four o'clock.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 This was a church school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 It was the Church of England school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Was it for boys and girls as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 A mixed school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Who used to go to this school with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Who used to take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
No one. No one. You see, there was one or two more in our family going you see, that's the way it was. Yes. They didn't all go there but there was one or two went you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Where did you have your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Twelve o'clock - just, we used to leave then at twelve. We'd go back -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You came home for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 At one thirty, and we were released again at four o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You say it was because you had an accident at the other school did you say?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
No, it was a child that hit me. A child hit me you see - I couldn't remember it and my mother said I came home one day with a black eye so she refused to allow to go any more. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What did you think of St John's school, did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well I thought St John's school was an ordinary school - was - exceptionally - what should I say - it was exceptionally good for the teachers and the master, they took great intere
st in the children, and what is more when the master came round I've heard him say many a time - if he wasn't quite suited with the progress of the children in that class - he would turn round to the - to the teacher, probably a male teacher, there was ma
l
e and female, he used to say sometimes, well I don't know, Mr So and so, he - he said, I don't think these childs - these children have any ambition whatsoever. He said, they don't appear to have a lot. And I once remember the schoolteacher remarking, he 
s
aid, no, he said, I don't think that, he said, things will have to alt - things will have to alter here. But I will say this, it's about one of the best ordinary schools that ever anyone could go to. They turned out - in those days there used to be about 
-
 I should say about six scholarships to be sat for, and - I think about everyone that ever entered the scholarship passed through - to wherever they were going. But of course you'd only - it only - unlike these days, there were only certain ones picked ou
t. But I'm afraid that - I was one of a big family that - if I had been picked out I daresay I could have passed, but - the root of the trouble was when you got out, was the finance - to keep you at the other school you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How did you feel about the
 teachers at St. John's, did you like them or dislike them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
I thought the teachers of both sexes, men and women, were excellent teachers for the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Did they at this school emphasise certain things as important in life, such as manners or tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Everything. Everything. You put that down - as practically everything that - that made - what you might term - how could we put it - a useful citizen. Put it that way, when you - you were taught to grow up to be a useful citizen, in every w
ay, both cleanliness - manners and anything that you could ever mention.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Punctuality, how about punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How about punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Punctual - they were very very strict on school. And if you didn't get there - we'll say you w
ere off one day, and there used to do what - what we used to call the school board man, and he was round at the door next door to see why you weren't at school. I think - I think they just allowed you one day's scope you see. And then they came to the doo
r
 to find out. He used to go round as near as I can tell you this - this official used to go around - I've seen - I appear to remember seeing him look at the register you see, and they would just mark out - mark off the people you see that was absent. One 
w
ould be red - in red I suppose, and one would be in black. But all the absentees you see - he took down, he made a note of them and he used to go to each individual house I presume and ask why they weren't at school. Some cases of course it may be a sickn
ess.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
How about ways of speaking, do you remember them helping you with your speech at all at that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Yes - they were - they were very very particular. They were very very particular - in the the articulation of your speech, you know, the kind of - a form of - elocution in a sense, because they used to get - they used to get you onto}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
your feet and read from books. And I remember being at that school when I was about - I got to be about - twelve year old, and there was a competi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 ti}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 on - as to who
 was the plainest speaker, and who was the best reader. And I happened - to be in this standard six, and I got through to the final - with another young man. And all the class had to listen you see while you read a paragraph from this book, quite remember
 
that. And - I was called upon first to read this paragraph from this book. And I read it - perfect - according to what they said - right through - every word clear, and then when I sat down they called upon the other one. He was a very good reader, but ha
l
fway through - halfway through this chapter whatever it was - he blundered and got on the wrong line, and he started again. So of course that went sadly against him as I'd made not one slight mistake, and I was claimed to be the champion reader, the excel
lent reader of the school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That's something to be proud of isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Yes, well - a good talker you see, just the same, everything was quite plain. Elocution. That's one thing they used to like - you to keep - to speak plainly. And there's one th
ing they always disliked children to do, and that was to tell tales, they told us - you must never tell tales. If ever anyone put their hand up you should never tell tales, sit down. That was one thing they were very very particular about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 If you did 
something the teachers disapproved of at St John's what would happen there, how did they punish the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well it was the cane. The cane on the hands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Would the girls get the same punishment as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well I couldn't exactly say wha
t the girls did. No. I don't think they got the cane, I think they were treated otherwise you see, as being -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 For what offences did the boys get punished at St John's school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes, you got that, that was recorded.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No, we didn't say for what offences.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Oh, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What sort of thing did they get caned for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well, for - impertinence or anything like that. Or if - if you defied them - in their teaching, you see. If you defied them in any way and they thought that you were - 
you were doing it for - what would you say - just because - you felt as though you didn't want to do it, then they would cane you for that, try to knock the hide off you, at the same time when they caned you you used to go back in the room and stand with 
y
our back to the class for at least one hour. After you'd been punished. It was really all in your interest when you come to think about it. I will say that. I always say and I admire St John's school and the master's name was - Braughton, his name was Bra
u
ghton and he also had two - two daughters teaching there, and they were very nice girls too. And all the women teachers were all so helpful to the children, in every shape and form. And there was one thing he was very determined to do, was Mr Braughton, h
e
'd partially - frighten the children - in trying to make them into very good scholars. That's one thing he did. And to this day, he's dead and gone and his daughters are all gone, I will say of this - that - his brutality in our - in our sense of mind in 
those days was the finest thing he could do for us, because he absolutely made us take it in, if it was possible for a child to take it in, that quantity of schooling that we were allowed in those days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did your parents show an interest in your school
work, did they ever ask you what you did at school or visit the school or meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Yes, they used to visit the - they - if they thought there was any trouble they would go along to the master you see. And then when we were at home, my fathe
r, he thought there was any difficulty - any difficulty in anything we didn't know he would try to show us a little bit, so we would be able to see how it was done and when we went back to school which was quite right. He was really taking an interest in 
you and helping you in your - in your school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own or not?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Oh I should say ninety percent of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Only in some instances. And they were very very few, they were in the minority my dear. And that will be - that sort of child - was a little bit sharper than the others - they used to place them in the front row and give them every chance to get o
n further still, if they were just a little bit in front, the others would be like you call - what you might call just a little bit backward behind them. If it was seen in a child - they would try to bring it out. But there wasn't very many, I remember wh
e
n I went to school I was approaching thirteen - you see, there was - there was two or three boys and two or three girls who were fairly clever. I wasn't really dumb myself but - I wasn't among that class you see, I didn't push myself forward, but - all my
 
schooling in my schooling days I think I - I could answer everything and anything they - they applied for me to an - to answer. I was a good reader, a good writer, I was a fairly good mathematician such as that, you see, the ordinary average schooltime wh
at do - what you - you have to pass.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Were there any gangs or groups in the school in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
No I wouldn't say so. They used to play out at - at the dinner times and the play times and - there was very little squabbling among the - the boys and the girls. They were very very friendly.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Just one or two who appeared to be very backward you see. You see, they - they were more or less - isolated by these people - the - these boys that
 was a little bit - more forward in the schooling. Buy apart from that they weren't really ignored, you see what I mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You didn't go to another school after this did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No, I finished from St John's school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You were fourteen when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 I was fourteen years when I left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Would you have stayed longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
I think so, but in those days my people - couldn't allow us, we must go out to earn a few shillings. You see, that's one thing my mothe
r said later on in life, she said, well - she said, there's only one thing I'm sorry for, she said, you've all done fairly well, she said, I'd like to have given you a little bit more }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 schooling}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 , but, she said, your father and me could not possibly do it. It took the money.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Did you attend any part time education afterwards, any evening classes or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
No, I never went to any evening classes whatsoever. All that everything we did - when we left school, and - it's a thing they don't p
ractice now, they've got so many opportunities, I think we had to more or less educate ourselves - from leaving school, you see, among your own - of course you were among your own family then you see, well I - although I'm my age now I was one of the youn
g
er end you see, and your sisters have many time come in at night and sit down with a pen and pencil and help you out with anything. You see, you did one help the other. It was a case of self - education after you left school, and that's what I calim I got
. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Do you have any regrets about your education? Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Oh I think yes, I think that was a wonderful school and I just got the ordinary elementary education, but I mean to say anyone that left that s
chool with an ordinary elementary education and they took in what that master who was so severe in some things, if they took in and he thought that when you left school you were reasonable fit to go out into the world, you'd have a fairly good elementary 
schooling
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Do you have any regrets then, would you have liked to have gone on further?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
I think I would. I would have liked to have gone on - but - of course I couldn't tell you now - why or what I would have liked to have gone in for. You see, I 
was a fairly good reader and a fairly good mathematician, of course it all depends - if we'd been allowed you see to go on then, and we'd been allowed to go to a school - a higher school, then of course you'd have made up your mind what you were going to 
do. But of course seeing that you never got that far it was a thing that never entered your head.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You said while you were at school you had a part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 To earn a little extra money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How did you get that job? It was the one at the grocers was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well, at the grocers - my - my brother you see used to work at the grocers and he got that job, he was older than, of course he'd now passed away, but he helped me to get that job and I used to go there and - w
hen I was about thirteen years of age, just to get this small sum of money you see, because I'm afraid that in those days before we grew up every shilling counted my dear, anyone knows that in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What exactly did you have to do in this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well you more or less run errands and such as that. You see - I'd go and solicit - soliciting orders and such as that. I used to go soliciting orders - you know, for - from - the different houses, and I used to take an order book when I was thirteen, 
and I did the same when I left when I went - when I left and I - I went to be a grocer and I did just the same. Go from house -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Were you an errand boy at the grocery }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 shop}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588  first, where were you an errand boy when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 When I - wher
e was I? I was at - at a grocery shop in - in Parkgate, yes, it was in Parkgate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What hours did you work, this part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well of course we left school at - four o'clock and we used to start I think about five. And I worked 'til about eight o'clock. Eight.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you work Sundays or Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Saturdays all day. Saturdays all day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
I don't suppose you had a half day did you, did you have any day that you didn't go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No. I always used to go - start on the Monday. You see, eac
h night to Friday and then all day Saturday, you see, and finish at Saturday night - somewhere about those - the - the shops used to close late you see, we used to - I used to finish at this shop about ten o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What were you paid for this part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
I was paid then - it jumped from about three shillings to three and sixpence when an errand boy. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you feel that was a fair wage or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well seeing as we couldn't claim any more I presume we must have done.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 I think you 
said you gave all the money to your mother and she had to use if for housekeeping, is that right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That is quite true.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Now how did you get on with the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Oh quite well. Very well indeed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How did your employer
 treat you, how did you feel about him and how did he treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well - he used to put faith in me, because when I was about thirteen year - thirteen years of age, when he - his assistant grocer used to go out of the shop, I used to go to the other s
ide of shop and I used to serve in his place, and he trusted me to do that, and you see all the money I took I counted what it - what - whatever the purchase came to I counted up, gave him the money and asked for the change. And he trusted me and he gave 
me that money, and I did that for twelve months. That was before left school. And I was an errand - errand boy really, in the meantime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How did you feel about the work, did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well - in one sense, I didn't care for the gro
cery trade. It was one trade that - it - it didn't appeal to me, didn't the grocery trade.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did this part time job alter your attitude to school in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Alter it in any way, what to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did the job alter your attitude to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Oh no, no, not in the slightest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
You didn't have any other part time job but when you left school you went in the grocers shop, is that right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes, I had a - I had another part time job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 I went as I told you to Arthur Sande
rs which is now Binns, don't you remember. And the only thing we used to do there of course when - we used to go at six o'clock when the shop was closing my dear, and then of course we used to go in what they called the box room where they parcelled up - 
a
ll the parcels you see, and then of course the manager used to come round or - his son, and at the finish you were all stood round in a ring you see at the top of the shop and all the parcels was placed so and so. There was a - all for the post there. The
r
e was this for - Carmel Road there, all the way, and they used to look round with his glasses on you see and say well, now you - you can go to the post - and you can take that and you can take that and then of course you got all your - you got all your pa
rcels and then you came out And when you delivered your parcels you went home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 This was when you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 And that was when I was still at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How did you get this job then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Well there was someone left and he told me, 
I went - I went to see if I could get it and - and said - they started me. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What hours did you work there, you just told me more or less in the evenings?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Yes. Just on six, we just used to go at six o'clock when the shop was closed and this -
 parcel porter you see, he was a young man seventeen, that's all he was, and he used to be in this - box room, packing room you see, and he packed all the - all the - the parcels you see, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 parcelled}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588  them up in boxes and - and otherwise, and they put the nam
es on, or - and all for the post you see, a lot of them used to go by post to the Post Office, and then all used to be carried out as I said - and he stood in the middle you see with all the parcels round him, the manager, Mr Sanders I can still see him, 
h
ow he used to be standing. Sometimes he would say to me - we used to wonder like who got the easy - I used to like to go to the Post Office usually because it wasn't very far away. Well sometimes he'd say to me, well you can go to the post you see, anothe
r time he might give me something that took me - almost two parts round the town delivering small parcels.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What sort of a business was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
It was a drapers business. It was established in the year 1770 on the front.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you work on Sundays, you wouldn't would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
No, but there's one great thing about that firm - to boys. Mr Sanders son who was very often there, and if he thought you were going to a place outside, same as Haughton, Haughton village outside here - he used to say, now - 
you're waiting for that parcel, he used to say - but - put probably threepence of fourpence in your hand, just get yourself a little supper he says, you're going to be working late. Now that was very good to a boy. That's quite true.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What hours did you work on Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
I used to work from - eight o'clock until six. And the same thing took place at six o'clock, you took out the parcels and then you were finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What were you paid there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 I was paid there three and sixpence. That was nights and Saturdays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you feel that was a fair wage or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well in those days - according to what - the money that was paid, that a man used to go out and work a full week for and I came to the conclusion that - for the work we're doing, par
ticularly at - at the drapers shop I was not badly paid. And that three and sixpence came in very useful - when you took it home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You gave that money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That mon - that money was given to my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How did you get on with the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Very well. Very well indeed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 And your employer treated you very well you told me?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes. That's quite true.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you like this work, did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 I liked it as a boy but I wouldn't h
ave cared to go in for the trade when I was older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did this job alter your attitude to school in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Not in the slightest. I thought - there's only one thing, I thought - that - my elementary schooling - helped me with the little position I had here before I was fourteen, that's what I thought.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 So were those the only two part time jobs you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That - those were the only two part time jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Then when you left school you went to train to be a grocer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 But you didn't stay there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
I didn't stay there because - the money wasn't big enough you see. You - for - for a full week you only got five shillings and four and ninepence. And if you had a day off they used to take a shilling off you if you were sick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How did you get this job at the grocers shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
It was advertised, and I - strange to say I left work - I left school at four pm on the Friday and on the Monday morning I started at that establishment at eight o'clock on the following Monday morning, two days later. Go on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
You started at the grocers shop, your first full time job just after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
The things you did were going out soliciting orders later on and serving in the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That's right. Right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What hours did you work there at the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 At the grocers shop - well - after I left school you meant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
From eight 'til seven, Monday and Tuesday. One o'clock Wednesday. Thursday and Friday eight o'clock. And Saturday ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you have holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 None whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 And what were you paid there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Five shillings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Is this your full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 At the full - at the grocers full time, yes, five shillings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 And you gave the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
I think you said you got on very well with the people that you worked with and you liked the man you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes. Perfect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 But you didn't like the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 So you left then and you went on the railway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 On the railway, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 In about 1910?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 And you were cleaning engines on the railway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That's right. Cleaning and firing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Working up to be a fireman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Working up to be a fireman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What hours did you work cleaning engines?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
From six until five, with half an hour for breakfast and one hour for dinner. Saturday morning twelve o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you have any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 None whatever, we used to have Good Friday and Christmas Day without pay.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What were you paid for cleaning engines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Ten shillings per week. Roughly speaking ten shillings per week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How did you get the job on the railway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 My father went, he took me. And I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 And what did you do as a fireman cleaning engines, what did you have to do?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Cleaning engines, well you used to - have these net cloths you see and paraffin, paraffin cleaned all the dirt off the wheels and everything and the frame. And then we used to polish it with another cloth. We used to do the boiler down with
 some grease known as tallow, you see, used some of that and we used to run about - rub all the dust off and then }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 polish}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588  it until it - it was quite clean, they were green you see and they were very pretty when they were finished. And we used to do as I say - about four per day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You told me what you were paid and you thought that was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 And you still gave the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How did you get on with the people you worked with at the railway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Excellent. I should say excellent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How did your employer treat you? Had you ever met him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes. Quite friendly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 How did you feel about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
I used to think he was more or less a gentleman and quite fair in all he dealt with.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you like the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 I did like the work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 In 1913 you went up to Garsdale was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 And you started as a fireman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
From 1913/14 I was fireman, I'd started being a fireman and you see I was sent away as a fireman, I'd just got to be a fireman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 And you used to travel on the lines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes, we were working passes trains.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What hours did you work there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Eleven hours - eleven hours per day. Always on days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 And sometimes you got a weekend from Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Owing to the frosts. To safeguard the locomotives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You had to go on Sunday sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes. Only with the frost, to safeguard the locomotive from freeze - from }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 freezing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 What were you paid now as a fireman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 A matter of about - twenty-one shilling
s per week I should say, the first - that was the first - that's the - the minimum pay, the minimum pay was - at one guinea per week, and from then onwards of course you rose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you feel that was a fair wage or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 At the time, yes. We - we w
ere looking for something better but of course as I said - when - when you talked to the chief men they used to say, well - how do you like this job? Oh it's a very nice one, but I don't like the money you see. Well of course he'd say - he - used to turn 
round and say, you can rise, you can rise, you see what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 And you kept the money because you were in digs then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
And you were still working with the same sort of people weren't you and you still liked them and you liked the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
And then you stayed at Garsdale and then you came back to Darlington in 1918, at the end of the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 At the end of - 1918, towards the end of the war, that was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 And you still were a fireman in Darlington?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 And then in 1924 you left the railway, is that right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 And you went to London and you were a warehouseman in London?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
And then you worked for the Darlington Corporation at the forge doing sort of semi skilled jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That's right, right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
And then you were off sick for a bit and then you went to the School Furnishing Company as a semi-skilled worker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 And you stayed there until you retired?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 At the retiring age. Have you got them all there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Would you have preferred another type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You served an apprenticeship didn't you for the railway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes. That was a - a - a form of apprenticeship. To - you - you were - you
 were apprenticed to being an engine driver you see, and you go from a cleaner to be a fireman, and then you pass - several examinations on locomotive, and then you were fully full - fully qualified to take charge of any locomotive.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you belong to any trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes I was in that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 And did you take a part in any of its activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Just now and again I was on a deputation, but I never work - I never went in for any positions such as secretary or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you fee
l that employers and workers had the same interests or different interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
I think they all had the same interests. They were very very friendly and very familiar with one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you feel that there were divisions of interests among worke
rs, some people say that in those days there was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 I wouldn't say so. I wouldn't say so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Did you feel that there divisions of interest among workers, some people say that in those days there was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers did you feel that or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No, I wouldn't say so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Would you 
say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well it - the only way it changed me was that - I was coming to year of discretion and I was looking ahead to see what I could make of my life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 And it made you look ahead at your life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes. Some form of incentive.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
You continued to live at home after you left school until you were twenty didn't you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Did starting full time work change your relationship with your parents or your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you spend your Sundays any differently, go to church or Sunday school?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No. We - took Sunday as a rest day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Did you take an interest in politics? What were your views, you said free trade and protection didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That
's right. And I believe in the free trade, the Liberals, because - protection put a tariff on the goods that was imported and the free trade allowed - imports to come in without any tax whatever. We used to think that the tax that was put on the protectio
n
, it was put up against the consumer. And then it went through the - the middle - man and - and it came to the con - to the consumer. And - I took the view, same as my father, that - we thought free trade was better, if - if goods were allowed to come in 
here they couldn't possibly put this tax on it they would when they - when the protection was on, it was like surtax coming in. And that would be handed over to the - what they call the middle men, and it would be handed over to the consumer eventually.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You said you didn't vote in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 No I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 And you didn't feel under any pressure from anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 And you weren't a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You told me somethin
g earlier of how you spent your spare time, did you continue to spend your spare time in the same way or did you do different things now you'd left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Much the same. In much the same way at home, much the same way. Only very quietly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 And you said you went out in the evening with boyfriends to the }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12937675\charrsid12588588 ice cream}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588  bar or for walks?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That's right. Just - strolling about, that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You didn't make any new friends at this time, boys or girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Not particularly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Except the boys you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 That's right. We'd sufficient friends without.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did you have any special friends at this time, boys or girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Possibly I used to have one, he used to go about more frequently with than another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Where would you go with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Well, pretty much the same, round the parks and just for walks and - the usual thing once more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did your parents meet your friends at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Yes, they used to - we used to exchange - visits to their homes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 Did they expect to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Not particular because they seemed to know that we had always - that we would be back by about nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1927463 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 You had to be back by nine o'clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10449094 AL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1991128\charrsid12588588 
Yes, and we generally got back about nine o'clock. Because in those days there was nothing on the street after nine.
